WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

2
00:00:22.564 --> 00:00:23.606
Move!

3
00:00:26.443 --> 00:00:27.527
Move!

4
00:00:28.445 --> 00:00:29.654
{\an8}Move!

5
00:00:29.738 --> 00:00:31.156
{\an8}NIIGATA PORT. 1868 (KEIO 4)

6
00:00:31.239 --> 00:00:32.949
{\an8}Move!

7
00:00:34.409 --> 00:00:35.910
Move!

8
00:00:37.954 --> 00:00:40.081
Move!

9
00:00:40.749 --> 00:00:41.916
What's going on?

10
00:00:42.500 --> 00:00:44.419
- What's happening?
- What?

11
00:00:48.673 --> 00:00:50.049
Osada!

12
00:00:54.804 --> 00:00:56.556
It's terrible.

13
00:00:56.639 --> 00:00:58.391
I told them we aren't prostitutes.

14
00:01:03.855 --> 00:01:05.065
Who?

15
00:01:05.148 --> 00:01:06.524
Who did this to you?

16
00:01:23.249 --> 00:01:24.626
Were they samurai?

17
00:01:24.709 --> 00:01:27.212
Osada. were they samurai?

18
00:01:35.094 --> 00:01:39.265
Lord Mizoguchi. this is the right moment
for us to make our move.

19
00:01:40.183 --> 00:01:43.061
{\an8}Our Northern Alliance Army
of the Ouetsu Domains has united.

20
00:01:43.144 --> 00:01:45.396
{\an8}and we must stop the Imperial Army
here in Echigo.

21
00:01:45.480 --> 00:01:47.148
Understood.

22
00:01:48.316 --> 00:01:50.485
It's clear like water.

23
00:01:50.568 --> 00:01:54.447
You. Shibata people. are all words
and no troops have been sent out.

24
00:01:54.531 --> 00:01:55.990
{\an8}I did send them out.

25
00:01:56.074 --> 00:01:59.452
{\an8}But they were hindered
by the peasants' uprising and…

26
00:01:59.536 --> 00:02:00.829
How surprising.

27
00:02:00.912 --> 00:02:04.290
{\an8}We should then line up those peasants
and behead them.

28
00:02:04.374 --> 00:02:06.668
Enough. Saito.

29
00:02:07.293 --> 00:02:09.129
Please. forgive his rudeness.

30
00:02:09.754 --> 00:02:11.256
However.

31
00:02:12.215 --> 00:02:15.885
the Imperial Army has already seized
Nagaoka Castle and is now at our gate.

32
00:02:16.511 --> 00:02:21.224
We would need the people of Shibata
to shed blood too this time.

33
00:02:21.307 --> 00:02:24.227
But. what will our Lord say?

34
00:02:27.272 --> 00:02:29.232
Then. Lord Mizoguchi…

35
00:02:29.899 --> 00:02:33.444
{\an8}We ourselves will head
to Shibata tomorrow.

36
00:02:34.112 --> 00:02:37.365
{\an8}and request the young Lord
directly to send out his troops.

37
00:02:38.074 --> 00:02:39.033
To the Lord?

38
00:02:39.617 --> 00:02:42.829
If the young Lord
refuses to send his troops.

39
00:02:43.413 --> 00:02:47.250
Shibata will be considered
a traitor to the Alliance.

40
00:02:48.501 --> 00:02:50.295
and we'll attack the castle.

41
00:02:58.595 --> 00:03:01.180
Watch your step.

42
00:03:02.599 --> 00:03:03.725
Hey.

43
00:03:05.643 --> 00:03:09.022
It's time for us to get into battle too.

44
00:03:09.105 --> 00:03:12.984
With those threats.
the Lord cannot refuse.

45
00:03:13.860 --> 00:03:15.445
- Sengoku…
- What?

46
00:03:15.528 --> 00:03:17.864
We might have to forget about women.

47
00:03:19.282 --> 00:03:21.075
Today is our last day.

48
00:03:23.536 --> 00:03:24.996
Oh. my. Zen.

49
00:03:25.079 --> 00:03:26.289
Oh. my.

50
00:03:26.372 --> 00:03:28.124
Again?

51
00:03:30.209 --> 00:03:32.921
Who is Zenemon Sengoku.
the Shibata vassal?

52
00:03:33.880 --> 00:03:34.881
What is it?

53
00:03:36.174 --> 00:03:37.258
What do you want me for?

54
00:03:41.679 --> 00:03:43.431
Die. you!

55
00:03:44.307 --> 00:03:45.767
Die!

56
00:03:51.564 --> 00:03:54.484
Die…

57
00:03:55.193 --> 00:03:59.239
Die…

58
00:04:11.042 --> 00:04:14.337
We came for a critical negotiation.
but now it's come down to a fight.

59
00:04:14.921 --> 00:04:16.881
Irie. how did this happen?

60
00:04:16.965 --> 00:04:19.509
It was due to our lack of supervision.

61
00:04:19.592 --> 00:04:20.802
Please. excuse us.

62
00:04:21.886 --> 00:04:24.722
Hey. let's go back to Shibata.

63
00:04:25.431 --> 00:04:28.268
Come on. let's go.

64
00:04:44.826 --> 00:04:46.327
Move aside! What is it?

65
00:04:48.579 --> 00:04:50.498
- Huh?
- Move!

66
00:04:53.084 --> 00:04:54.669
No. come back.

67
00:04:56.796 --> 00:04:57.714
Osada…

68
00:05:07.348 --> 00:05:08.349
Move!

69
00:05:08.933 --> 00:05:10.852
He's going to be executed in Shibata.

70
00:05:11.561 --> 00:05:13.313
You're not to interfere!

71
00:05:23.281 --> 00:05:25.033
Are you deaf. woman?

72
00:05:25.700 --> 00:05:27.952
I said. move!

73
00:05:28.786 --> 00:05:29.829
Go.

74
00:05:32.165 --> 00:05:33.166
Osada.

75
00:05:48.056 --> 00:05:51.350
{\an8}SHIBATA EXECUTION GROUNDS

76
00:05:53.061 --> 00:05:55.354
Hey… hey.

77
00:05:58.066 --> 00:06:01.277
You. what did you do?

78
00:06:06.741 --> 00:06:09.827
I'm about to die. why should I answer?

79
00:06:10.453 --> 00:06:13.790
Since you're about to die.
there's no need to act all mighty.

80
00:06:13.873 --> 00:06:16.584
No!

81
00:06:16.667 --> 00:06:19.629
Go ahead!

82
00:06:31.682 --> 00:06:33.351
It's because of the war.

83
00:06:35.228 --> 00:06:36.938
Because the war is going to start.

84
00:06:38.272 --> 00:06:40.775
things are going to get tough.

85
00:06:48.282 --> 00:06:49.283
Yeah.

86
00:07:06.217 --> 00:07:07.844
<i>In the fourth year of Keio.</i>

87
00:07:08.928 --> 00:07:14.142
<i>as the samurai era that had lasted
for centuries was coming to an end.</i>

88
00:07:14.225 --> 00:07:17.603
<i>Japan was immersed in the Boshin War.</i>

89
00:07:25.736 --> 00:07:29.782
<i>The new government forces led by Satsuma
and Choshu support the Imperial Court.</i>

90
00:07:29.866 --> 00:07:32.410
<i>They call themselves the Imperial Army.</i>

91
00:07:32.952 --> 00:07:37.123
<i>The faction wishing for the former
Tokugawa Shogunate to survive</i>

92
00:07:37.707 --> 00:07:40.501
<i>were made to surrender.</i>

93
00:07:47.758 --> 00:07:49.385
BOSHIN WAR

94
00:07:50.761 --> 00:07:52.013
KYOTO

95
00:07:52.096 --> 00:07:55.808
BATTLE OF TOBA-FUSHIMI

96
00:07:55.892 --> 00:07:57.143
EDO

97
00:07:57.226 --> 00:08:00.771
FALL OF EDO. BATTLE OF UENO

98
00:08:00.855 --> 00:08:02.190
NAGAOKA - SHIBATA

99
00:08:02.273 --> 00:08:06.861
BATTLE OF NAGAOKA CASTLE

100
00:08:07.445 --> 00:08:09.363
<i>In the center of the Nagaoka domain.</i>

101
00:08:09.447 --> 00:08:11.782
<i>clans close to the Tokugawa Shogunate</i>

102
00:08:12.366 --> 00:08:15.411
<i>formed the Northern Alliance Army
of the Ouetsu Domains</i>

103
00:08:15.495 --> 00:08:18.289
<i>and confronted the Imperial Army.</i>

104
00:08:20.333 --> 00:08:23.252
<i>Opportunistic. indecisive.
and avoiding war.</i>

105
00:08:23.336 --> 00:08:25.671
<i>Shibata. a small domain in Echigo.</i>

106
00:08:26.297 --> 00:08:30.468
<i>was asked to take a stance
once and for all.</i>

107
00:08:40.311 --> 00:08:42.688
<i>Either to fight with the Alliance</i>

108
00:08:42.772 --> 00:08:45.149
<i>or to side with the Imperial Army.</i>

109
00:08:45.233 --> 00:08:48.569
<i>Shibata was made to make a decision.</i>

110
00:09:13.678 --> 00:09:16.305
What is taking the Chief so long?

111
00:09:17.056 --> 00:09:18.599
We. the people of Shibata.

112
00:09:18.683 --> 00:09:21.018
should rise up
for the sake of Echigo. too.

113
00:09:21.102 --> 00:09:24.480
Otherwise. we won't be able
to confront the Alliance!

114
00:09:24.564 --> 00:09:25.523
That's true.

115
00:09:25.606 --> 00:09:28.818
If we don't fight the Imperial Army now.
then when?

116
00:09:28.901 --> 00:09:31.904
There's no point in waiting
for the Chief's decision.

117
00:09:31.988 --> 00:09:35.241
We'll go to the castle tomorrow
and request a military deployment.

118
00:09:35.741 --> 00:09:36.742
Yes.

119
00:09:37.368 --> 00:09:38.578
Who's there?

120
00:09:42.832 --> 00:09:44.000
Irie?

121
00:09:44.625 --> 00:09:47.962
It came to my ears
that some rebels were plotting something.

122
00:09:48.588 --> 00:09:50.047
Plotting?

123
00:09:50.131 --> 00:09:51.674
Our clan isn't moving at all…

124
00:09:51.757 --> 00:09:55.261
The clan's movements
are up to the Chief to decide.

125
00:09:55.344 --> 00:09:57.847
You have no say in this.

126
00:09:57.930 --> 00:10:00.266
If you are not willing to obey.

127
00:10:01.767 --> 00:10:03.060
you'll be arrested.

128
00:10:03.144 --> 00:10:04.228
Hey!

129
00:10:16.365 --> 00:10:18.451
We'd be expected to fight
for our hometown.

130
00:10:18.534 --> 00:10:21.078
Haven't you learnt a thing in this dojo?

131
00:10:21.829 --> 00:10:24.540
Marrying into a Chief's family
can change a person a lot. right?

132
00:10:24.624 --> 00:10:26.292
What did you…?

133
00:10:29.587 --> 00:10:31.756
Hey. Irie. look!

134
00:10:33.299 --> 00:10:34.675
A fire.

135
00:10:34.759 --> 00:10:36.010
Put it out!

136
00:10:38.054 --> 00:10:39.138
Hurry!

137
00:10:42.850 --> 00:10:44.060
It's going beyond the walls!

138
00:10:44.143 --> 00:10:45.770
- Fire!
- Fire!

139
00:10:45.853 --> 00:10:47.438
Put it out!

140
00:10:53.986 --> 00:10:57.073
- Put the fire out first.
- Bring water.

141
00:10:58.032 --> 00:10:59.867
Keep going!

142
00:10:59.950 --> 00:11:03.329
Keep going!

143
00:11:03.412 --> 00:11:05.456
Give up. you bitch!

144
00:11:05.539 --> 00:11:06.957
Let go!

145
00:11:07.041 --> 00:11:10.127
What's wrong with setting
a murderer's house on fire?

146
00:11:10.211 --> 00:11:11.796
This woman started the fire?

147
00:11:12.380 --> 00:11:13.964
It's a prostitute.

148
00:11:14.048 --> 00:11:16.258
A favored customer
made her have an abortion.

149
00:11:16.342 --> 00:11:18.219
Looks like she was holding a grudge.

150
00:11:18.886 --> 00:11:21.847
Favored? Not at all. you scoundrel.

151
00:11:21.931 --> 00:11:24.266
He killed my child!

152
00:11:24.350 --> 00:11:26.060
I'm going to kill him!

153
00:11:26.143 --> 00:11:27.937
I'm telling you to give up!

154
00:11:28.020 --> 00:11:29.105
Let me go!

155
00:11:31.607 --> 00:11:33.192
Please. sir…

156
00:12:00.136 --> 00:12:02.930
Hello. miss. What did you do?

157
00:12:03.013 --> 00:12:06.016
You've got a lovely face.

158
00:12:06.100 --> 00:12:07.435
Come here.

159
00:12:07.518 --> 00:12:10.855
Why are you getting away?
You're going to die soon anyway.

160
00:12:10.938 --> 00:12:12.690
No need to be afraid.

161
00:12:12.773 --> 00:12:15.109
Aren't you happy?

162
00:12:15.192 --> 00:12:17.069
Where did you just touch me?

163
00:12:17.153 --> 00:12:19.155
Let me see…

164
00:12:27.246 --> 00:12:28.706
You're too noisy. baldy.

165
00:12:29.457 --> 00:12:30.916
Get some sleep.

166
00:12:41.302 --> 00:12:42.970
Align your stance!

167
00:12:43.679 --> 00:12:44.805
{\an8}NAGAOKA CASTLE
IMPERIAL ARMY HEADQUARTERS

168
00:12:44.889 --> 00:12:45.973
{\an8}Align!

169
00:12:46.557 --> 00:12:47.683
{\an8}Fire!

170
00:12:49.101 --> 00:12:51.812
You've got to practice
until you can move properly.

171
00:12:52.438 --> 00:12:56.984
The Alliance is not the one
to give up either.

172
00:12:57.693 --> 00:13:00.070
{\an8}We thought they'd just
abandon this castle and run.

173
00:13:00.154 --> 00:13:02.698
{\an8}but they're still resisting.

174
00:13:03.824 --> 00:13:05.201
Yamagata.

175
00:13:05.284 --> 00:13:08.954
I'm getting tired of the war at Echigo.

176
00:13:09.038 --> 00:13:11.248
{\an8}This country must
be changed from the grounds.

177
00:13:11.332 --> 00:13:12.791
{\an8}It won't be that easy. right?

178
00:13:12.875 --> 00:13:14.126
{\an8}Indeed. but…

179
00:13:14.210 --> 00:13:17.546
{\an8}in a few more months.
Echigo will be covered in snow.

180
00:13:17.630 --> 00:13:20.424
If we don't settle this quickly.
we will lose our advantage.

181
00:13:20.508 --> 00:13:21.717
Then.

182
00:13:22.760 --> 00:13:24.553
this port is key.

183
00:13:25.429 --> 00:13:27.097
Niigata Port?

184
00:13:27.181 --> 00:13:30.226
The Alliance's weapons
cross the sea and arrive to this port.

185
00:13:30.309 --> 00:13:33.187
Then they cross the river
to Nagaoka and Aizu.

186
00:13:33.771 --> 00:13:35.231
In other words.

187
00:13:35.814 --> 00:13:38.442
this is the heart of the Alliance.

188
00:13:38.526 --> 00:13:41.362
The defenses at their heart
will be strong.

189
00:13:41.445 --> 00:13:44.240
I've heard the Alliance
has split their troops. though…

190
00:13:44.323 --> 00:13:47.785
So. what is surrounding this heart is…

191
00:13:48.452 --> 00:13:50.120
Shibata?

192
00:13:50.704 --> 00:13:53.916
But aren't they part of the Alliance too?

193
00:13:53.999 --> 00:13:56.460
I've heard their lord is still a child.

194
00:13:57.002 --> 00:13:58.712
The winds are changing.

195
00:14:12.977 --> 00:14:16.105
How did I do. Takumi? Did you see that?

196
00:14:17.940 --> 00:14:21.861
My Lord. the Alliance
will come to this castle tomorrow.

197
00:14:21.944 --> 00:14:25.322
At this point.
we should send out the troops…

198
00:14:25.406 --> 00:14:26.532
What?

199
00:14:26.615 --> 00:14:30.786
{\an8}What with the Alliance?
Don't make me laugh.

200
00:14:30.870 --> 00:14:32.997
{\an8}Nagaoka has relentlessly
taken our rights away.

201
00:14:33.080 --> 00:14:35.624
Didn't they rule over Echigo
as if it were their own?

202
00:14:35.708 --> 00:14:37.710
Indeed. but this is a decisive moment.

203
00:14:38.210 --> 00:14:39.795
If Echigo joined them too…

204
00:14:40.546 --> 00:14:42.965
The Imperial Army will win the battle.

205
00:14:44.466 --> 00:14:46.594
We might as well ride on their coattails.

206
00:14:46.677 --> 00:14:48.304
But. my Lord.

207
00:14:48.387 --> 00:14:52.182
With all due respect.
if we refrain from sending our troops.

208
00:14:52.266 --> 00:14:54.476
the Alliance will attack
the castle tomorrow…

209
00:14:54.560 --> 00:14:56.687
Let's turn a blind eye
on some sacrifices. then.

210
00:14:57.646 --> 00:14:59.481
The Imperial Army will come to help us.

211
00:15:00.816 --> 00:15:01.859
But…

212
00:15:01.942 --> 00:15:04.570
Anyway. drive the Alliance away neatly.

213
00:15:05.195 --> 00:15:07.072
That is your damn job.

214
00:15:19.001 --> 00:15:22.338
There's no doubt about it. That's him.

215
00:15:33.599 --> 00:15:34.808
Who are you?

216
00:15:36.518 --> 00:15:37.937
It hurts.

217
00:15:38.020 --> 00:15:39.063
What are you doing?

218
00:15:39.146 --> 00:15:42.149
I've been looking for you.

219
00:15:42.232 --> 00:15:44.401
I have to save you now.

220
00:15:45.235 --> 00:15:48.697
What. is this kid
your little brother or something?

221
00:15:49.365 --> 00:15:52.201
Wait. do you know this dirty brat?

222
00:15:52.284 --> 00:15:53.869
This is funny.

223
00:15:53.953 --> 00:15:55.829
Hey. boy. Come and help me too.

224
00:15:59.792 --> 00:16:01.669
It hurts!

225
00:16:01.752 --> 00:16:03.253
I beg you. come here.

226
00:16:03.337 --> 00:16:04.672
Hey. come here.

227
00:16:04.755 --> 00:16:05.965
Brother.

228
00:16:06.048 --> 00:16:07.800
It's this way.

229
00:16:07.883 --> 00:16:09.969
Wait for me. I'm going to.

230
00:16:10.052 --> 00:16:11.220
Wait! Hey!

231
00:16:11.303 --> 00:16:13.472
Hey! Come here!

232
00:16:14.348 --> 00:16:16.934
Hey. brat! Are you going to leave me?

233
00:16:17.768 --> 00:16:20.270
You! What are you doing?

234
00:16:20.354 --> 00:16:22.064
Aren't you commoners?

235
00:16:22.147 --> 00:16:24.233
Brother. brother!

236
00:16:27.236 --> 00:16:30.072
Wait! Hey!

237
00:16:30.155 --> 00:16:31.740
- Brother!
- I'm sorry. kid!

238
00:16:34.076 --> 00:16:35.744
Move!

239
00:16:35.828 --> 00:16:37.162
Isn't he one of the prisoners?

240
00:16:37.246 --> 00:16:38.956
- Hurry up!
- Bastard!

241
00:16:40.666 --> 00:16:43.127
- Where are you running to?
- You…

242
00:16:46.964 --> 00:16:48.048
Hold him down!

243
00:16:48.799 --> 00:16:50.175
Let go!

244
00:16:58.642 --> 00:17:03.564
I'm bringing a direct message
from the Imperial Army Chief. Yamagata.

245
00:17:06.275 --> 00:17:09.278
{\an8}"The reason I'm asking to have
an audience with Lord Naomasa

246
00:17:09.361 --> 00:17:14.199
{\an8}is because I will be sending our advance
party to Shibata Castle tomorrow morning."

247
00:17:21.248 --> 00:17:23.042
The Imperial Army. to the Lord?

248
00:17:23.709 --> 00:17:25.753
They probably intend
to propose an alliance.

249
00:17:26.420 --> 00:17:28.422
Isn't that convenient?

250
00:17:28.505 --> 00:17:29.882
Our Lord wished to join them…

251
00:17:29.965 --> 00:17:31.759
No. don't be stupid.

252
00:17:31.842 --> 00:17:35.262
The Alliance will arrive
at the castle tomorrow.

253
00:17:35.345 --> 00:17:39.099
They'll run into each other.
There'll be a battle in the castle.

254
00:17:42.436 --> 00:17:45.481
Chief. what do you plan to do?

255
00:17:46.982 --> 00:17:47.983
Chief…

256
00:18:23.393 --> 00:18:24.520
Chief…

257
00:18:27.397 --> 00:18:29.942
My father was a strict person.

258
00:18:31.777 --> 00:18:36.532
I was trained here
because those who govern

259
00:18:36.615 --> 00:18:38.742
must also be skilled at the sword.

260
00:18:40.244 --> 00:18:43.080
With all due respect.
what did you call me for today?

261
00:18:43.163 --> 00:18:46.291
I was wondering if there's anypne
who'd risk their lives for Shibata!

262
00:18:46.375 --> 00:18:47.376
Pardon?

263
00:18:47.459 --> 00:18:51.338
What if you asked your retainers.
Lord Washio?

264
00:18:51.421 --> 00:18:54.591
Everyone mentioned your name unanimously.

265
00:18:55.217 --> 00:18:58.554
Wait. you want me to send my clan
against the Alliance?

266
00:19:02.099 --> 00:19:03.976
They can discuss it with you there.

267
00:19:06.937 --> 00:19:10.399
Hey. what is that? It's huge.

268
00:19:10.482 --> 00:19:11.650
Brother!

269
00:19:11.733 --> 00:19:13.527
So it's going to be saw-cutting.

270
00:19:14.111 --> 00:19:16.530
They'll be delivering a spectacle.

271
00:19:18.824 --> 00:19:20.784
Why are you going to saw me too?

272
00:19:20.868 --> 00:19:22.619
Shut up! You're just as guilty.

273
00:19:22.703 --> 00:19:24.329
I didn't do anything!

274
00:19:24.413 --> 00:19:26.623
Hey. boss. Please spare me the saw.

275
00:19:26.707 --> 00:19:29.251
I'd rather be stabbed with a spear.

276
00:19:29.334 --> 00:19:31.086
Hey. do it.

277
00:19:45.225 --> 00:19:46.518
Wait!

278
00:19:48.270 --> 00:19:49.646
Halt the execution!

279
00:19:50.272 --> 00:19:51.773
What?

280
00:19:59.489 --> 00:20:01.325
We. the Shibata Domain.

281
00:20:01.408 --> 00:20:03.869
as part of the Alliance.
will go battle the Imperial Army.

282
00:20:04.953 --> 00:20:06.079
Battle?

283
00:20:06.663 --> 00:20:08.624
The infantry will be sent out tomorrow.

284
00:20:08.707 --> 00:20:12.085
but that will leave
our defense short-handed.

285
00:20:12.169 --> 00:20:14.338
That's where you lowlifes
are going to help.

286
00:20:15.130 --> 00:20:17.716
Do you mean we're going to battle?

287
00:20:18.300 --> 00:20:21.970
You're going to defend a fortress
within the domain from the Imperial Army.

288
00:20:23.764 --> 00:20:25.349
Hey. boss.

289
00:20:25.432 --> 00:20:27.434
That's a ridiculous joke.

290
00:20:27.517 --> 00:20:29.144
It's not a joke.

291
00:20:30.437 --> 00:20:34.233
You are all criminals.
so you're going to fight for us.

292
00:20:34.858 --> 00:20:37.069
Once the mission is accomplished.

293
00:20:38.904 --> 00:20:41.240
all of you will be pardoned
for your crimes.

294
00:20:41.990 --> 00:20:43.242
What?

295
00:20:44.117 --> 00:20:45.118
We'll be pardoned?

296
00:20:45.911 --> 00:20:47.579
For real?

297
00:20:47.663 --> 00:20:49.915
Will we be allowed to go back home?

298
00:20:49.998 --> 00:20:52.084
That is what the Chief said himself.

299
00:20:53.043 --> 00:20:58.048
Did you hear that. boy?
We're going to do this.

300
00:20:58.131 --> 00:21:01.134
We'll be pardoned!

301
00:21:03.637 --> 00:21:04.596
This is no joke.

302
00:21:06.223 --> 00:21:08.600
You. the Shibata samurai.
What did you do to my wife?

303
00:21:11.186 --> 00:21:13.438
I won't bow to your demands.
even if I died for it.

304
00:21:15.107 --> 00:21:16.400
Shut up!

305
00:21:16.483 --> 00:21:17.651
Brother!

306
00:21:17.734 --> 00:21:20.070
- This lowlife is acting all mighty.
- Stop. Arai!

307
00:21:20.153 --> 00:21:21.488
But he killed Sengoku!

308
00:21:21.571 --> 00:21:24.199
The soldiers will finish him.
No need to rush it.

309
00:21:33.333 --> 00:21:35.919
I'm saying I'll show mercy.

310
00:21:36.003 --> 00:21:37.129
even to a lowlife like you.

311
00:21:37.212 --> 00:21:38.422
If you refuse.

312
00:21:39.006 --> 00:21:41.216
I'll throw you into a separate cell…

313
00:21:45.637 --> 00:21:47.848
<i>Together with the ones sick with cholera.</i>

314
00:21:48.890 --> 00:21:50.892
<i>Once you catch it. it's over.</i>

315
00:21:50.976 --> 00:21:53.895
<i>You'll throw up everything
that's inside you and die.</i>

316
00:21:54.604 --> 00:21:56.857
What are you going to choose?

317
00:22:08.869 --> 00:22:11.830
Boss. what do we do with the woman?

318
00:22:15.500 --> 00:22:16.918
Can you cook?

319
00:22:18.837 --> 00:22:20.422
Of course I can.

320
00:22:20.505 --> 00:22:21.923
I can dance too.

321
00:22:23.091 --> 00:22:24.092
In that case. get ready.

322
00:22:24.801 --> 00:22:28.263
The ten of you are to be known as
the Ouetsu Alliance Army Suicide Squad.

323
00:22:28.805 --> 00:22:29.890
Get ready!

324
00:22:44.780 --> 00:22:50.243
{\an8}WEST - FUKUSHIMAGATA
NORTH - ECHIGO HIGHWAY. SHIBATA

325
00:22:51.036 --> 00:22:53.789
Why is he the only one handcuffed?

326
00:22:54.748 --> 00:22:57.375
Isn't it because he's dangerous?

327
00:22:59.086 --> 00:23:01.546
Have you heard about
the ten beheadings of Yonekura?

328
00:23:02.130 --> 00:23:03.840
Was he the one who commited them?

329
00:23:04.716 --> 00:23:06.218
Isn't he an evil one?

330
00:23:06.301 --> 00:23:07.469
Fool.

331
00:23:07.552 --> 00:23:09.971
Everyone here is evil.

332
00:23:10.764 --> 00:23:11.973
No doubt about that.

333
00:23:12.557 --> 00:23:14.101
A bandit who killed his landlord.

334
00:23:14.184 --> 00:23:16.019
the arson woman.

335
00:23:16.103 --> 00:23:18.188
a survivor of a mass family suicide.

336
00:23:18.271 --> 00:23:20.023
the samurai murderer.

337
00:23:20.107 --> 00:23:21.358
and to top it off.

338
00:23:21.441 --> 00:23:25.278
the pervert monk who abused
the daughter of a parishioner.

339
00:23:26.822 --> 00:23:29.783
I don't want to be told that
by a renowned scammer.

340
00:23:29.866 --> 00:23:31.034
That's scary.

341
00:23:32.786 --> 00:23:35.831
Irie. why are we raising
the flag of Nagaoka?

342
00:23:36.498 --> 00:23:38.542
To be seen as Shibata's infantry.

343
00:23:38.625 --> 00:23:40.168
It was decided by the Alliance.

344
00:23:40.252 --> 00:23:42.879
So you're involved with the Alliance
to that extent…

345
00:23:42.963 --> 00:23:44.172
Is that what you desired?

346
00:23:57.769 --> 00:23:59.146
We'll leave our horses here.

347
00:24:04.401 --> 00:24:05.944
Is the fortress up here?

348
00:24:08.321 --> 00:24:09.739
Still a long way to go?

349
00:24:27.841 --> 00:24:28.884
Halt.

350
00:24:32.470 --> 00:24:35.599
This is the fortress we must protect.

351
00:25:05.337 --> 00:25:08.757
{\an8}DAY ONE
KEIO 4. 22ND DAY OF THE 7TH MONTH

352
00:25:27.859 --> 00:25:29.027
Good job.

353
00:25:29.110 --> 00:25:32.072
Finally. It was heavy.
but we've gotten up.

354
00:25:32.155 --> 00:25:34.574
You made the right decision.

355
00:25:34.658 --> 00:25:36.326
Let's go pay respects to the young Lord.

356
00:25:36.409 --> 00:25:37.494
About that…

357
00:25:38.036 --> 00:25:40.497
He hasn't been feeling well
since yesterday.

358
00:25:41.039 --> 00:25:42.624
Let go. you insolents!

359
00:25:42.707 --> 00:25:44.876
Why should I be hiding?

360
00:25:45.460 --> 00:25:48.630
It's because of the cholera.
There are infected people in the castle.

361
00:25:48.713 --> 00:25:52.092
I won't talk to you! Get Takumi here!

362
00:25:52.759 --> 00:25:54.844
I'll shoot you. scoundrels!

363
00:25:54.928 --> 00:25:58.265
<i>Since he's an important person
about to go to war.</i>

364
00:25:58.348 --> 00:25:59.224
<i>he needs to rest.</i>

365
00:25:59.307 --> 00:26:00.517
What?

366
00:26:02.394 --> 00:26:03.520
What a pity.

367
00:26:03.603 --> 00:26:06.189
The Lord has approved of the march. too.

368
00:26:07.148 --> 00:26:08.483
Food supplies will arrive soon.

369
00:26:08.566 --> 00:26:11.069
Alcohol goes first.

370
00:26:11.653 --> 00:26:12.988
Alcohol?

371
00:26:13.071 --> 00:26:15.407
We're going to battle together.

372
00:26:15.490 --> 00:26:18.243
We can't get to it
without drinking first. right?

373
00:26:19.911 --> 00:26:21.204
Indeed.

374
00:26:21.288 --> 00:26:23.206
Let's get ready then.

375
00:26:27.669 --> 00:26:30.088
Feel free to have fun today.

376
00:26:30.171 --> 00:26:32.632
We'll send them off happily tomorrow.

377
00:26:32.716 --> 00:26:34.843
But tomorrow. the Imperial Army…

378
00:26:34.926 --> 00:26:36.094
Don't worry about that.

379
00:26:36.928 --> 00:26:40.473
That's why we're sending off
a suicide squad.

380
00:26:52.235 --> 00:26:53.236
All right?

381
00:26:53.862 --> 00:26:56.781
You'll become free
only if you fight for Shibata.

382
00:26:56.865 --> 00:26:58.950
Don't you forget that.

383
00:26:59.034 --> 00:27:01.286
You swallowed up everything.
didn't you. boss?

384
00:27:01.369 --> 00:27:03.455
Leave it to us and don't worry.

385
00:27:04.122 --> 00:27:05.373
Right. boy?

386
00:27:05.457 --> 00:27:07.876
Let me be clear from the beginning.

387
00:27:07.959 --> 00:27:10.962
If just one of you tried to sneak out.

388
00:27:11.046 --> 00:27:12.797
your pardons will be revoked.

389
00:27:13.631 --> 00:27:14.466
Revoked?

390
00:27:15.216 --> 00:27:16.843
What?

391
00:27:16.926 --> 00:27:18.845
You didn't mention that last night.
did you?

392
00:27:18.928 --> 00:27:20.847
Should any of you plan to rebel.

393
00:27:20.930 --> 00:27:23.141
I'll have you kill yourselves!

394
00:27:24.851 --> 00:27:26.227
Isn't that plain and simple?

395
00:27:30.732 --> 00:27:33.401
Kobure. free him too.

396
00:27:34.444 --> 00:27:35.653
Yes.

397
00:27:53.380 --> 00:27:55.048
Hurry up!

398
00:27:55.757 --> 00:27:57.509
Carry on!

399
00:27:57.592 --> 00:27:59.135
Get back once you've put it down.

400
00:28:00.929 --> 00:28:02.263
Let's line them up here.

401
00:28:05.767 --> 00:28:08.228
Hurry up. we don't have time!

402
00:28:08.812 --> 00:28:11.022
Don't slack off. come on!

403
00:28:11.106 --> 00:28:13.274
You. load it there.

404
00:28:14.109 --> 00:28:16.027
Get back immediately!

405
00:28:17.487 --> 00:28:18.613
Get back now!

406
00:28:36.047 --> 00:28:38.133
If the Imperial Army
were to take this fortress.

407
00:28:38.216 --> 00:28:39.884
they would need to cross that bridge.

408
00:28:39.968 --> 00:28:43.471
We'll threaten them with our guns and stop
them right before the bridge somehow.

409
00:28:44.139 --> 00:28:46.141
There are ten of them.
including the woman.

410
00:28:46.641 --> 00:28:48.393
I wonder how they'll perform.

411
00:28:48.476 --> 00:28:50.729
I bet they'll go all out.

412
00:28:52.063 --> 00:28:53.898
You. the acquitted one.

413
00:28:54.983 --> 00:28:56.735
The two of you can handle this.

414
00:28:59.738 --> 00:29:01.614
You're not putting your back into it.

415
00:29:01.698 --> 00:29:03.241
Our back? What do you mean?

416
00:29:03.324 --> 00:29:04.743
Put your back into it.

417
00:29:05.410 --> 00:29:07.871
Well. we can't expect a long battle.

418
00:29:07.954 --> 00:29:09.581
It'll be over in two days at most.

419
00:29:09.664 --> 00:29:11.791
The Chief is aware of that. too.

420
00:29:11.875 --> 00:29:14.544
As soon as the castle town is secured.
we'll light the signal fire.

421
00:29:14.627 --> 00:29:17.839
That will mean it's over.

422
00:29:18.465 --> 00:29:21.384
Then we might as well
just destroy the bridge.

423
00:29:24.512 --> 00:29:25.346
What do you mean?

424
00:29:25.930 --> 00:29:27.307
Stop it.

425
00:29:28.308 --> 00:29:30.769
If there's no bridge.
the Imperial Army will have to detour.

426
00:29:30.852 --> 00:29:33.521
We'd be able to stop them
for a day or two.

427
00:29:40.737 --> 00:29:41.696
Irie!

428
00:29:42.280 --> 00:29:45.366
You were in fact the son of the doctor
in the castle town.

429
00:29:45.450 --> 00:29:48.077
You tried to board a foreign ship
and get to Russia?

430
00:29:48.661 --> 00:29:49.662
"Oroshiya"?

431
00:29:50.580 --> 00:29:53.249
Foreign trade would be impossible
without that bridge!

432
00:29:54.292 --> 00:29:56.920
We must think about
the aftermath of the war.

433
00:30:20.485 --> 00:30:23.613
Hey. Noro. Where are you going?

434
00:30:24.489 --> 00:30:25.615
Noro.

435
00:30:27.951 --> 00:30:30.453
If you act on your own.
you'll get us killed.

436
00:30:38.127 --> 00:30:40.213
What are you doing?

437
00:30:43.883 --> 00:30:45.051
What?

438
00:30:49.305 --> 00:30:50.849
Is it good?

439
00:30:59.774 --> 00:31:02.193
What's with this horrible water?

440
00:31:09.993 --> 00:31:12.328
Heave-ho.

441
00:31:16.332 --> 00:31:17.500
There you go.

442
00:31:22.714 --> 00:31:24.340
Good. let's go.

443
00:31:27.260 --> 00:31:28.261
Okay.

444
00:31:41.149 --> 00:31:43.192
About the bridge we talked about.

445
00:31:43.276 --> 00:31:45.111
I agree that we should think about trade.

446
00:31:45.653 --> 00:31:47.405
but if the war escalates. we'll have to--

447
00:31:47.488 --> 00:31:49.866
That's not going to happen!

448
00:31:49.949 --> 00:31:50.825
Why not?

449
00:31:51.659 --> 00:31:52.744
We're soldiers.

450
00:31:53.620 --> 00:31:56.497
We haven't even fought yet.
and you're starting to chicken out.

451
00:31:56.581 --> 00:31:58.625
If we were to be cowards.

452
00:31:59.667 --> 00:32:02.503
the criminals wouldn't even need to work.

453
00:32:12.430 --> 00:32:13.932
It's so good.

454
00:32:15.141 --> 00:32:16.559
So good.

455
00:32:17.393 --> 00:32:19.562
I'd like my deceased wife and brother

456
00:32:19.646 --> 00:32:22.273
to try this and eat until they're full.

457
00:32:22.357 --> 00:32:24.359
Enough with the hardships.

458
00:32:25.610 --> 00:32:27.820
By the way.

459
00:32:27.904 --> 00:32:30.698
what were you planning to do
in "Oroshiya"?

460
00:32:33.159 --> 00:32:35.036
To learn medicine.

461
00:32:36.245 --> 00:32:37.664
Medicine?

462
00:32:39.332 --> 00:32:41.918
That was a big move.

463
00:32:42.001 --> 00:32:43.836
It's illegal to leave Japan or your clan.

464
00:32:43.920 --> 00:32:45.964
and attempting to flee
to a foreign country

465
00:32:46.047 --> 00:32:47.924
is forbidden beyond all measure!

466
00:32:48.716 --> 00:32:49.550
So. mister.

467
00:32:50.885 --> 00:32:52.303
What did you do?

468
00:32:53.554 --> 00:32:54.555
Well.

469
00:32:55.223 --> 00:32:57.141
I didn't do anything wrong.

470
00:32:57.684 --> 00:33:00.478
The person I liked was a samurai's wife…

471
00:33:00.561 --> 00:33:02.188
Fool.

472
00:33:02.271 --> 00:33:05.441
Being handsome is a sin from birth. right?

473
00:33:05.525 --> 00:33:06.985
No doubt.

474
00:33:07.068 --> 00:33:10.571
You are the greatest villain.

475
00:33:11.072 --> 00:33:12.448
That's right.

476
00:33:13.032 --> 00:33:14.993
Noro. would you bring me some more food?

477
00:33:15.702 --> 00:33:17.829
- I'll go…
- I'll go.

478
00:33:17.912 --> 00:33:21.374
Is it okay? Thank you. mister.

479
00:33:21.958 --> 00:33:25.628
The only good person
among all of us is Noro.

480
00:33:25.712 --> 00:33:27.880
Idiots can be sinners.

481
00:33:33.344 --> 00:33:36.556
By the way.
why would you want to go to "Oroshiya"?

482
00:33:36.639 --> 00:33:38.057
Huh?

483
00:33:38.141 --> 00:33:39.851
I had already asked you. right?

484
00:33:39.934 --> 00:33:41.060
Brother!

485
00:33:45.189 --> 00:33:46.399
Move. boss.

486
00:33:46.482 --> 00:33:48.109
What?

487
00:33:50.069 --> 00:33:52.280
That tattooed bastard actually did it!

488
00:33:52.363 --> 00:33:54.282
- I'll kill him.
- Go after him.

489
00:33:54.365 --> 00:33:55.366
Damn!

490
00:34:16.345 --> 00:34:17.847
There he is!

491
00:34:17.930 --> 00:34:19.766
- Hey!
- Don't run!

492
00:34:19.849 --> 00:34:21.684
- Hey!
- You there!

493
00:34:22.643 --> 00:34:24.520
- Hey!
- Hurry!

494
00:34:29.025 --> 00:34:30.151
Stop!

495
00:34:30.234 --> 00:34:32.570
If you run. you'll be executed.

496
00:34:50.838 --> 00:34:53.549
- Hey. wait!
- Wait!

497
00:34:54.133 --> 00:34:56.094
- They're here.
- They're here!

498
00:34:57.845 --> 00:34:59.472
Wait.

499
00:35:00.056 --> 00:35:01.766
- Look.
- Wait.

500
00:35:05.978 --> 00:35:07.522
- The Imperial Army…
- What?

501
00:35:07.605 --> 00:35:08.773
The Imperial Army?

502
00:35:08.856 --> 00:35:10.149
Let's return and shut the gate.

503
00:35:10.233 --> 00:35:12.860
We won't make it to the gate.
Hide somewhere!

504
00:35:26.332 --> 00:35:28.459
We just need to cross that
to get to Shibata.

505
00:35:29.544 --> 00:35:32.547
Lord Sera. the flag…

506
00:35:32.630 --> 00:35:33.756
Flag?

507
00:35:35.716 --> 00:35:38.469
It's the flag of Nagaoka.

508
00:35:39.303 --> 00:35:40.555
That's strange.

509
00:35:41.639 --> 00:35:43.766
The Alliance shouldn't be in this pass.

510
00:35:45.935 --> 00:35:47.478
Don't worry.

511
00:35:47.562 --> 00:35:49.689
The gate is open. let's get in.

512
00:36:13.588 --> 00:36:15.423
Brother. it's a mantis.

513
00:36:16.299 --> 00:36:17.300
Idiot…

514
00:36:24.640 --> 00:36:27.393
Who's there? Show yourselves!

515
00:36:36.819 --> 00:36:38.613
- Go.
- Yes.

516
00:36:45.661 --> 00:36:48.831
We know you're hiding there.

517
00:36:56.923 --> 00:36:58.758
It's this boorish fellow.

518
00:36:58.841 --> 00:37:01.135
Who are you? Say your name!

519
00:37:01.219 --> 00:37:04.555
You're the ones
who are trying to trespass here!

520
00:37:05.348 --> 00:37:06.807
Will you identify yourselves first?

521
00:37:08.559 --> 00:37:10.853
We're the advance party
of the Imperial Army.

522
00:37:11.854 --> 00:37:14.190
We're here to pay our respects
to Lord Naomasa.

523
00:37:14.273 --> 00:37:15.608
head of the Mizoguchi clan.

524
00:37:16.734 --> 00:37:18.527
We are not here to fight.

525
00:37:19.737 --> 00:37:21.405
You're not here to fight?

526
00:37:21.489 --> 00:37:22.865
Indeed.

527
00:37:22.949 --> 00:37:24.492
What do you mean?

528
00:37:24.575 --> 00:37:26.869
Why did you come then?

529
00:37:27.828 --> 00:37:28.871
Here's my chance!

530
00:37:36.796 --> 00:37:39.423
What do you think? This was my 13th.

531
00:37:39.966 --> 00:37:41.550
Who's next?

532
00:37:42.134 --> 00:37:44.428
Kill them!

533
00:38:22.883 --> 00:38:24.218
You. over here!

534
00:38:57.418 --> 00:38:58.336
14th!

535
00:39:26.739 --> 00:39:28.366
- Let go!
- Help!

536
00:39:29.742 --> 00:39:31.827
- Let go!
- Help!

537
00:39:31.911 --> 00:39:33.412
Let go!

538
00:39:33.496 --> 00:39:37.750
Spare… my life…

539
00:39:55.643 --> 00:39:58.979
What are you doing. mister? It's a battle!

540
00:40:04.110 --> 00:40:05.778
I know that!

541
00:40:07.196 --> 00:40:08.197
Move!

542
00:40:11.242 --> 00:40:12.243
Move!

543
00:40:13.035 --> 00:40:16.455
Is there something
we've never seen before?

544
00:40:17.206 --> 00:40:20.835
- Stop. we'll be punished.
- What are you saying? It's a battle.

545
00:40:26.257 --> 00:40:28.008
This is no joke…

546
00:40:29.093 --> 00:40:31.387
To die in a place like this…

547
00:40:34.223 --> 00:40:36.267
Wait. I'm going too.

548
00:41:02.626 --> 00:41:04.420
That idiot…

549
00:41:07.798 --> 00:41:08.924
Ready!

550
00:41:12.928 --> 00:41:14.054
What are you doing?

551
00:41:16.640 --> 00:41:18.142
Washio!

552
00:41:37.661 --> 00:41:38.746
Boss. behind you!

553
00:41:56.305 --> 00:41:57.681
Lord Sera!

554
00:41:59.350 --> 00:42:00.726
Lord Sera…

555
00:42:01.519 --> 00:42:02.811
Lord Sera.

556
00:42:08.692 --> 00:42:09.777
Lord Sera.

557
00:42:17.868 --> 00:42:18.869
Lord Sera…

558
00:42:22.540 --> 00:42:24.833
You!

559
00:42:24.917 --> 00:42:27.753
Brother. we won't make it now.
Let's retreat!

560
00:42:27.836 --> 00:42:29.463
But Lord Sera…

561
00:42:30.798 --> 00:42:32.633
Go. let's get away!

562
00:42:33.342 --> 00:42:35.010
Brother. quick!

563
00:42:41.559 --> 00:42:43.727
- Retreat!
- Retreat!

564
00:42:47.314 --> 00:42:49.233
Wash your face and try again.

565
00:42:49.316 --> 00:42:52.528
We're the Ouetsu Alliance Army
Suicide Squad.

566
00:42:53.445 --> 00:42:54.822
Remember that!

567
00:43:04.623 --> 00:43:05.916
It hurts…

568
00:43:07.835 --> 00:43:12.423
You. I'll kill you…

569
00:43:12.506 --> 00:43:14.049
Do you want to die?

570
00:43:14.633 --> 00:43:16.760
Damn.

571
00:43:17.344 --> 00:43:19.805
It's the tattooed bastard's fault.

572
00:43:19.888 --> 00:43:23.225
I'll cut him down…

573
00:43:23.309 --> 00:43:24.768
It hurts.

574
00:43:24.852 --> 00:43:27.771
Be an adult and don't move.

575
00:43:30.107 --> 00:43:33.444
Give up. you traitor.

576
00:43:33.527 --> 00:43:36.238
Do anything uncalled for again.

577
00:43:36.322 --> 00:43:38.824
and I'll cut you into pieces.

578
00:43:39.617 --> 00:43:41.118
Brother!

579
00:43:41.702 --> 00:43:43.412
Go there.

580
00:43:47.625 --> 00:43:49.960
It's mine…

581
00:43:50.044 --> 00:43:52.046
Get in.

582
00:44:05.351 --> 00:44:07.227
Why do you want to die early?

583
00:44:10.439 --> 00:44:12.608
Notice has been sent to other lands.

584
00:44:13.525 --> 00:44:16.028
You lowlifes don't have anywhere
to run away.

585
00:44:20.741 --> 00:44:24.578
It must have been unfair for your wife.

586
00:44:26.080 --> 00:44:27.873
But if you fulfill your duty here.

587
00:44:27.956 --> 00:44:29.625
you can go back to your wife.

588
00:44:29.708 --> 00:44:31.835
I cannot change what happened
even if I get back.

589
00:44:36.382 --> 00:44:37.549
It won't change anything.

590
00:44:42.846 --> 00:44:45.516
There's no way I can fight for Shibata.

591
00:44:48.811 --> 00:44:51.230
If you don't like it.
do whatever pleases you.

592
00:44:54.608 --> 00:44:55.609
In that case…

593
00:44:56.819 --> 00:44:58.153
you shall die.

594
00:44:58.779 --> 00:45:00.030
Brother!

595
00:45:02.449 --> 00:45:04.243
You saved me.

596
00:45:05.452 --> 00:45:07.121
I'll turn a blind eye this time.

597
00:45:08.372 --> 00:45:09.790
But if you do it again.

598
00:45:12.000 --> 00:45:13.585
I won't hesitate to kill you.

599
00:45:24.179 --> 00:45:25.722
Let's go.

600
00:45:30.978 --> 00:45:33.480
And you are the Special Forces?

601
00:45:34.398 --> 00:45:37.192
You fled and came back.

602
00:45:37.276 --> 00:45:38.861
Shame on you!

603
00:45:38.944 --> 00:45:40.279
Wait. Iwamura.

604
00:45:41.530 --> 00:45:43.323
They were not heading to battle.

605
00:45:43.407 --> 00:45:44.241
It's no surprise.

606
00:45:47.619 --> 00:45:51.832
By the way. is it true
that the enemies were not from Shibata.

607
00:45:51.915 --> 00:45:54.126
but the infantry from Nagaoka?

608
00:45:54.209 --> 00:45:55.419
Yes.

609
00:45:56.044 --> 00:45:58.797
The thieves were using this seal.

610
00:46:02.217 --> 00:46:03.927
I've heard Nagaoka is gathering troops

611
00:46:04.011 --> 00:46:06.263
to retake this castle.

612
00:46:06.346 --> 00:46:08.849
But I didn't know they still
had resources to defend Shibata.

613
00:46:11.852 --> 00:46:15.689
Shibata is a key place to the Alliance.

614
00:46:18.692 --> 00:46:22.029
We ought to change the winds
no matter what.

615
00:46:23.405 --> 00:46:25.616
First. it's this fortress.

616
00:46:25.699 --> 00:46:28.535
SHIBATA

617
00:46:35.876 --> 00:46:38.337
Looks like they arrived
to the castle yesterday.

618
00:46:41.590 --> 00:46:44.927
Looks like they were trying to find
the Suicide Squad's location.

619
00:46:46.178 --> 00:46:49.264
And where's my husband fighting?

620
00:46:49.848 --> 00:46:52.184
Isn't it natural that I want to know?

621
00:46:55.020 --> 00:46:57.689
Women shouldn't interfere in politics.

622
00:46:59.525 --> 00:47:02.694
Is my father planning
to call off the engagement?

623
00:47:02.778 --> 00:47:03.987
Kana…

624
00:47:04.071 --> 00:47:08.033
Perhaps he lost interest in Lord Irie
after being humiliated in the sword fight?

625
00:47:08.742 --> 00:47:10.285
I'm the only one who should

626
00:47:10.369 --> 00:47:11.495
be worried about that!

627
00:47:22.047 --> 00:47:23.173
Do not misbehave.

628
00:47:28.303 --> 00:47:31.848
You should leave this to your father.

629
00:47:36.520 --> 00:47:37.521
Kana?

630
00:47:39.856 --> 00:47:41.650
Kana? What's wrong?

631
00:47:44.945 --> 00:47:45.988
Kana!

632
00:47:46.780 --> 00:47:49.449
I brought onigiris.

633
00:47:49.533 --> 00:47:51.285
Here you go.

634
00:47:51.368 --> 00:47:53.412
Good job.

635
00:47:53.495 --> 00:47:58.041
Good job. everyone from the Alliance.

636
00:47:58.625 --> 00:48:01.587
We've got more onigiris.

637
00:48:03.338 --> 00:48:05.090
Food. alcohol.

638
00:48:05.173 --> 00:48:07.509
and a woman.

639
00:48:12.180 --> 00:48:15.475
I didn't think it was a good idea before.

640
00:48:15.559 --> 00:48:18.645
I underestimated Shibata.

641
00:48:19.646 --> 00:48:21.690
And why was that?

642
00:48:22.816 --> 00:48:25.569
We shall prepare for the battle soon.

643
00:48:26.111 --> 00:48:27.654
I can't wait for the infantry…

644
00:48:27.738 --> 00:48:30.782
This is going to be all. Lord Mizoguchi.

645
00:48:31.366 --> 00:48:36.747
I thought about asking the Young Lord
directly about his intentions.

646
00:48:36.830 --> 00:48:38.081
Huh?

647
00:48:38.665 --> 00:48:40.584
But our Lord is sick…

648
00:48:40.667 --> 00:48:44.504
If you say the Lord might have
changed his mind or something.

649
00:48:44.588 --> 00:48:47.758
and another promise is broken.

650
00:48:47.841 --> 00:48:48.800
I won't bear it.

651
00:48:53.805 --> 00:48:57.351
In any case. bring the Young Lord here.

652
00:48:58.602 --> 00:49:00.020
Up until now.

653
00:49:02.064 --> 00:49:04.274
I haven't moved a step.

654
00:49:11.239 --> 00:49:13.367
Irie. isn't the signal fire lit yet?

655
00:49:16.161 --> 00:49:19.331
I have no doubt we'll see it today.

656
00:49:21.083 --> 00:49:24.753
DAY TWO
KEIO 4. 23RD DAY OF THE 7TH MONTH

657
00:50:01.873 --> 00:50:02.916
Hey.

658
00:50:03.709 --> 00:50:07.003
You're disgusting. go somewhere.

659
00:50:11.591 --> 00:50:14.886
Don't be ashamed.
isn't he a cute little brother?

660
00:50:15.595 --> 00:50:16.596
Noro.

661
00:50:16.680 --> 00:50:18.890
Go inside and have your lunch.

662
00:50:30.026 --> 00:50:31.153
Eat.

663
00:50:37.075 --> 00:50:37.909
I don't want it.

664
00:50:38.577 --> 00:50:39.661
Eat.

665
00:50:39.745 --> 00:50:41.872
Why are you so foolish to stay hungry?

666
00:50:41.955 --> 00:50:43.373
Are you an idiot?

667
00:50:43.874 --> 00:50:44.750
You're not my wife…

668
00:50:44.833 --> 00:50:47.711
The samurai of Shibata abused her. right?

669
00:50:47.794 --> 00:50:49.671
It came to my ears already.

670
00:50:49.755 --> 00:50:51.423
What are you?

671
00:50:51.506 --> 00:50:52.632
Taking down your enemies

672
00:50:52.716 --> 00:50:54.176
might feel good. but…

673
00:50:54.968 --> 00:50:57.304
What is your wife going to do on her own?

674
00:50:58.555 --> 00:50:59.890
She's the wife of a commoner.

675
00:50:59.973 --> 00:51:02.225
She wasn't accomodated to begin with.

676
00:51:03.351 --> 00:51:05.729
If her husband returns as a criminal.

677
00:51:05.812 --> 00:51:07.981
she could go no further
than being a prostitute or a beggar.

678
00:51:08.064 --> 00:51:09.941
- You bastard…
- In other words…

679
00:51:10.692 --> 00:51:12.778
gain your pardon. no matter what.

680
00:51:12.861 --> 00:51:15.155
and get back to your wife.

681
00:51:18.033 --> 00:51:19.534
So. why don't you eat some?

682
00:51:34.299 --> 00:51:35.592
It stinks.

683
00:51:36.301 --> 00:51:38.136
The food will go to waste.

684
00:51:38.220 --> 00:51:40.055
Stay out!

685
00:51:43.308 --> 00:51:44.226
Wait.

686
00:51:44.309 --> 00:51:46.978
What if I gave you a hug later?

687
00:51:52.108 --> 00:51:53.819
Do you know that boy?

688
00:51:56.112 --> 00:51:58.782
He was with a famous fireworks master
in Shibata.

689
00:52:00.075 --> 00:52:01.785
But he's not there anymore.

690
00:52:02.577 --> 00:52:03.912
He's not?

691
00:52:03.995 --> 00:52:05.956
He died in a fireworks accident.

692
00:52:06.873 --> 00:52:08.792
Looks like that kid caused it.

693
00:52:08.875 --> 00:52:11.294
I heard it was terrible
for his parents and siblings.

694
00:52:15.882 --> 00:52:17.300
Do I look that much like him?

695
00:52:18.176 --> 00:52:19.219
What?

696
00:52:20.512 --> 00:52:21.555
Do I look like him?

697
00:52:21.638 --> 00:52:23.390
The man who died.

698
00:52:33.567 --> 00:52:34.985
Not at all.

699
00:52:35.068 --> 00:52:36.236
What was that?

700
00:52:39.948 --> 00:52:42.242
That foolish-looking bunch

701
00:52:42.325 --> 00:52:45.662
managed to defeat the Imperial Army. led
by the renowned Satsuma and Choshu clans.

702
00:52:45.745 --> 00:52:46.997
It's fun.

703
00:52:47.581 --> 00:52:49.499
If we don't take the challenge
while there's a chance

704
00:52:49.583 --> 00:52:51.501
we'll be left behind.

705
00:52:52.085 --> 00:52:53.253
What do you think?

706
00:52:53.336 --> 00:52:55.422
What are you betting on it?

707
00:52:55.505 --> 00:52:58.008
None of us have any money.

708
00:52:58.675 --> 00:53:00.802
Don't be fools.

709
00:53:02.262 --> 00:53:05.307
Aren't there some people here
who are drinking a lot?

710
00:53:08.018 --> 00:53:10.353
You don't know when to stop.

711
00:53:10.437 --> 00:53:12.731
Are foreign countries that good?

712
00:53:12.814 --> 00:53:15.025
We may have outdated weapons.

713
00:53:15.108 --> 00:53:16.985
but in a battle. spirit is key.

714
00:53:17.068 --> 00:53:18.361
That's the samurai way!

715
00:53:20.280 --> 00:53:21.323
That hurts…

716
00:53:21.406 --> 00:53:24.826
Hey. old man.
Make him understand the samurai way.

717
00:53:31.875 --> 00:53:34.336
Trying to explain
the benefits of foreign nations

718
00:53:34.419 --> 00:53:36.504
to those shouting. "Expel the barbarians"

719
00:53:36.588 --> 00:53:38.548
will obviously get you punched.

720
00:53:42.385 --> 00:53:45.388
This telescope is a foreign invention.

721
00:53:46.056 --> 00:53:48.475
When there's war
they rely on imported goods.

722
00:53:48.558 --> 00:53:50.936
yet they shout to expel the foreigners.

723
00:53:51.019 --> 00:53:53.605
I wonder if that's the samurai way.

724
00:53:57.317 --> 00:53:59.402
What's that?

725
00:54:00.070 --> 00:54:01.279
What's wrong?

726
00:54:06.493 --> 00:54:09.037
Are they digging gold?

727
00:54:10.538 --> 00:54:11.706
I'm in.

728
00:54:19.965 --> 00:54:22.550
Good. It's a half.

729
00:54:24.177 --> 00:54:25.387
Is that alright?

730
00:54:26.054 --> 00:54:28.807
You're broke. right?
What are you going to bet?

731
00:54:31.643 --> 00:54:33.812
Come and get me. you bastard.

732
00:54:35.397 --> 00:54:36.481
Let's play.

733
00:54:47.659 --> 00:54:49.119
There it is!

734
00:54:49.202 --> 00:54:51.746
The winner takes it all. right?

735
00:54:51.830 --> 00:54:53.748
An even number with double ones.

736
00:54:53.832 --> 00:54:54.958
What?

737
00:54:55.041 --> 00:54:56.418
Aren't those doubles?

738
00:54:58.086 --> 00:54:59.254
No…

739
00:54:59.796 --> 00:55:02.340
That's bad. boss.

740
00:55:02.424 --> 00:55:05.010
That's how the game is. you never know.

741
00:55:05.093 --> 00:55:07.095
Winds are suddenly in my favor. right?

742
00:55:07.178 --> 00:55:09.723
Make sure to change the lookout duty.

743
00:55:09.806 --> 00:55:12.058
or your boss. Oroshiya will get mad.

744
00:55:12.142 --> 00:55:13.977
Then. I'm off with this.

745
00:55:19.065 --> 00:55:20.275
It hurts…

746
00:55:25.530 --> 00:55:28.908
You cheating bastard…

747
00:55:29.743 --> 00:55:31.745
What? No. it wasn't me…

748
00:55:33.955 --> 00:55:35.999
It's fine. go kill him.

749
00:55:38.001 --> 00:55:40.295
You made a fool of me!

750
00:55:41.087 --> 00:55:42.422
Hey.

751
00:55:45.550 --> 00:55:48.595
You did it.

752
00:55:49.179 --> 00:55:51.264
Stop. what were you doing gambling?

753
00:55:51.347 --> 00:55:54.059
Let go. Washio!

754
00:55:55.310 --> 00:55:57.103
You're a samurai too.

755
00:55:58.813 --> 00:56:01.232
We can't allow these lowlifes to make

756
00:56:01.316 --> 00:56:03.401
a fool out of any of us!

757
00:56:03.985 --> 00:56:06.321
Lowlifes?

758
00:56:06.946 --> 00:56:09.282
Hey. did you hear that?

759
00:56:09.908 --> 00:56:10.950
This man here is looking down

760
00:56:11.034 --> 00:56:12.577
on us as if we were horse dung.

761
00:56:12.660 --> 00:56:15.413
- Calm down. you too!
- Of course!

762
00:56:16.039 --> 00:56:18.833
Just the sight of you criminals
is an insult!

763
00:56:18.917 --> 00:56:21.044
Then why don't you just crucify us all?

764
00:56:21.127 --> 00:56:23.296
Yes. kill us if you hate us that much!

765
00:56:23.379 --> 00:56:25.924
In that case.
the Lord of Shibata would be in trouble.

766
00:56:26.007 --> 00:56:27.300
What?

767
00:56:27.383 --> 00:56:29.761
It's impossible with this man.

768
00:56:30.303 --> 00:56:32.639
You cannot defeat the Imperial Army.

769
00:56:32.722 --> 00:56:33.932
What did you say?

770
00:56:34.015 --> 00:56:35.517
Enough already!

771
00:56:36.101 --> 00:56:36.976
Enough!

772
00:56:37.060 --> 00:56:38.853
Leave them to me!

773
00:56:38.937 --> 00:56:40.522
I'll cut them down!

774
00:56:41.022 --> 00:56:43.566
How exciting.

775
00:57:03.086 --> 00:57:04.462
Let me cool down.

776
00:57:05.213 --> 00:57:06.381
Get down quick!

777
00:57:08.049 --> 00:57:09.050
Over there.

778
00:57:17.809 --> 00:57:19.936
I don't get what you're thinking.

779
00:57:20.019 --> 00:57:21.312
Arai!

780
00:57:21.396 --> 00:57:22.981
This is a really important mission

781
00:57:23.064 --> 00:57:23.940
the Chief gave us!

782
00:57:24.023 --> 00:57:25.525
I know that!

783
00:57:25.608 --> 00:57:29.446
But having to sleep and wake up
next to these lowlifes

784
00:57:29.529 --> 00:57:31.322
is driving me crazy!

785
00:57:38.413 --> 00:57:42.041
Once our mission is over.
they're to be silenced anyway. right?

786
00:57:42.625 --> 00:57:44.836
You can kill them
however you prefer. then.

787
00:57:44.919 --> 00:57:47.005
You'll be able to do as you like.

788
00:57:58.516 --> 00:58:01.019
They're here!

789
00:58:01.102 --> 00:58:03.229
To arms!

790
00:58:05.857 --> 00:58:08.860
The Imperial Army is here!

791
00:58:16.868 --> 00:58:19.287
Hey! What's going on?

792
00:58:19.370 --> 00:58:20.663
Fire!

793
00:58:25.627 --> 00:58:27.253
Hey!

794
00:58:27.837 --> 00:58:29.088
Hey…

795
00:58:29.172 --> 00:58:30.131
Kogure!

796
00:58:30.215 --> 00:58:31.674
Free me!

797
00:58:31.758 --> 00:58:33.593
Hey! Free me!

798
00:58:33.676 --> 00:58:35.553
Kogure. are you okay?

799
00:58:35.637 --> 00:58:38.139
Hey. free me!

800
00:58:38.223 --> 00:58:40.725
Unlock this…

801
00:58:40.808 --> 00:58:42.602
Hey!

802
00:58:44.270 --> 00:58:45.230
Hey.

803
00:58:45.313 --> 00:58:47.106
You're right. we should have fled.

804
00:58:47.190 --> 00:58:49.943
What? Get the key from him
and unlock this.

805
00:58:50.026 --> 00:58:51.569
Hurry!

806
00:58:52.570 --> 00:58:53.530
I'm sorry…

807
00:59:00.411 --> 00:59:02.455
What the heck are you doing?

808
00:59:02.539 --> 00:59:05.375
Get ready. quick! Bring the arms!

809
00:59:05.458 --> 00:59:07.502
Our numbers won't make a difference
in this fight.

810
00:59:12.590 --> 00:59:14.759
We can't do this. Irie. Let's retreat!

811
00:59:14.842 --> 00:59:16.010
Don't be an idiot!

812
00:59:16.094 --> 00:59:18.179
In that case let's send these men.

813
00:59:18.263 --> 00:59:19.389
We'll get to the castle town…

814
00:59:19.472 --> 00:59:20.807
How could you be so cowardly?

815
00:59:20.890 --> 00:59:22.809
It's cowardly. but anyway they're…

816
00:59:28.690 --> 00:59:32.235
Arai! Are you okay?

817
00:59:35.989 --> 00:59:39.117
Irie. we can't win even if we fought back.

818
00:59:39.200 --> 00:59:41.828
Even if that's so. what can we do?

819
00:59:43.037 --> 00:59:44.581
I've got an idea.

820
00:59:49.210 --> 00:59:50.044
Fire!

821
00:59:50.628 --> 00:59:51.629
Fire!

822
01:00:05.018 --> 01:00:06.894
- Fire!
- Fire!

823
01:00:11.566 --> 01:00:13.359
- Go!
- Yes.

824
01:00:28.166 --> 01:00:29.208
Sir Masatora…

825
01:00:29.876 --> 01:00:31.628
The tower gate is open.

826
01:00:32.879 --> 01:00:34.088
Did they run away?

827
01:00:35.131 --> 01:00:37.008
They must still be nearby.

828
01:00:37.925 --> 01:00:40.303
- We won't go back without a souvenir. go!
- Yes.

829
01:00:43.931 --> 01:00:45.475
- The back-ups will await here.
- Yes.

830
01:00:51.939 --> 01:00:53.358
What's that smoke?

831
01:01:43.950 --> 01:01:44.951
Wait.

832
01:01:46.411 --> 01:01:48.162
The troops at the back aren't coming.

833
01:01:57.547 --> 01:02:00.425
The bandits are lurking around.
don't let your guards down!

834
01:02:37.420 --> 01:02:39.213
We were waiting for you.

835
01:02:40.006 --> 01:02:41.466
That's the 30th.

836
01:02:44.051 --> 01:02:46.012
Watch out! We're allies!

837
01:02:46.095 --> 01:02:47.263
What the heck?

838
01:03:01.277 --> 01:03:03.446
That forest! Aim for that forest!

839
01:03:03.529 --> 01:03:04.489
Yes.

840
01:03:04.572 --> 01:03:06.324
- Shoot there!
- Quick!

841
01:03:07.617 --> 01:03:10.912
We're marching too!

842
01:03:25.218 --> 01:03:28.346
Can we really use these things?

843
01:03:29.305 --> 01:03:30.598
We have no choice.

844
01:03:35.061 --> 01:03:37.021
I can't see because of the damn smoke.

845
01:03:37.104 --> 01:03:38.481
They made too much of it.

846
01:03:42.568 --> 01:03:44.028
Here they come.

847
01:03:47.824 --> 01:03:49.158
Up there!

848
01:03:51.577 --> 01:03:52.870
We missed.

849
01:03:55.540 --> 01:03:57.959
- Fire!
- Fire!

850
01:04:02.046 --> 01:04:04.465
- Fire!
- Fire!

851
01:04:10.763 --> 01:04:12.890
Noro. are you okay?

852
01:04:14.267 --> 01:04:17.770
We're not made for this.

853
01:04:20.565 --> 01:04:23.317
Idiot! Where are you going?

854
01:04:23.401 --> 01:04:25.152
One. two…

855
01:04:26.529 --> 01:04:28.239
One. two…

856
01:04:29.949 --> 01:04:32.285
- Fire!
- Fire!

857
01:04:44.839 --> 01:04:45.840
Hey.

858
01:04:47.508 --> 01:04:49.552
Hey!

859
01:04:52.179 --> 01:04:53.598
It hurts…

860
01:04:57.143 --> 01:04:58.185
Hey!

861
01:04:59.395 --> 01:05:00.855
Are you okay?

862
01:05:06.652 --> 01:05:08.279
We won't get anywhere without more guns.

863
01:05:08.362 --> 01:05:09.447
Where are you going?

864
01:05:10.281 --> 01:05:11.324
Hey!

865
01:05:12.491 --> 01:05:13.576
Go!

866
01:05:15.453 --> 01:05:17.705
Don't come near me!

867
01:05:17.788 --> 01:05:19.165
Don't come!

868
01:05:20.374 --> 01:05:21.918
Let's open it!

869
01:05:39.143 --> 01:05:41.020
There's nothing we can do. let's run away.

870
01:05:46.108 --> 01:05:48.194
Hey. what are you doing?

871
01:05:48.819 --> 01:05:50.071
Let's go. quick.

872
01:06:14.595 --> 01:06:17.181
It hurts!

873
01:06:18.099 --> 01:06:19.183
That was close.

874
01:06:20.226 --> 01:06:22.103
What are you doing?

875
01:06:22.186 --> 01:06:23.854
You. stay here. I'll go.

876
01:06:23.938 --> 01:06:26.315
I don't want to be left alone
with this madman!

877
01:06:26.399 --> 01:06:28.859
It hurts!

878
01:06:28.943 --> 01:06:30.695
I thought we were partners!

879
01:07:01.809 --> 01:07:02.935
Arai!

880
01:07:05.855 --> 01:07:08.816
Irie. hang in there!

881
01:07:25.124 --> 01:07:26.333
Nimaime!

882
01:07:26.917 --> 01:07:28.669
Are you okay?

883
01:07:29.378 --> 01:07:32.882
- It hurts…
- Move.

884
01:07:32.965 --> 01:07:35.468
Does anyone know where Noro is?

885
01:07:35.551 --> 01:07:37.803
We can't help with that right now.

886
01:07:41.515 --> 01:07:44.101
Hey! Where are the weapons?

887
01:08:00.326 --> 01:08:04.121
Brother. move!

888
01:08:28.687 --> 01:08:29.980
What did you do?

889
01:08:35.152 --> 01:08:37.363
Noro. lend me that!

890
01:08:37.446 --> 01:08:38.864
- Brother?
- Give it.

891
01:08:40.074 --> 01:08:41.408
Move!

892
01:08:52.586 --> 01:08:53.504
Get away from me!

893
01:09:01.720 --> 01:09:02.930
Tsujigiri. get away!

894
01:09:10.521 --> 01:09:11.689
Throw it. idiot!

895
01:09:37.423 --> 01:09:40.759
Hurry up!

896
01:09:40.843 --> 01:09:42.970
Reload. quick!

897
01:09:43.053 --> 01:09:46.265
Shoot! Hurry up and shoot!

898
01:09:46.348 --> 01:09:49.143
Lord Masataka. over there!

899
01:09:51.770 --> 01:09:55.316
Kill me…

900
01:09:57.484 --> 01:09:59.278
Kill me!

901
01:10:00.446 --> 01:10:01.655
Brother…

902
01:10:08.329 --> 01:10:09.830
Wake up.

903
01:10:09.914 --> 01:10:11.582
Come on. hang in there.

904
01:10:13.167 --> 01:10:16.712
Let's have some drinks. then.
To celebrate.

905
01:10:17.296 --> 01:10:20.299
What drinks? We've suffered casualties.

906
01:10:20.382 --> 01:10:23.052
So we deal with it by drinking.

907
01:10:26.013 --> 01:10:29.141
Look at what happened to Nimaime's face…

908
01:10:29.225 --> 01:10:32.853
Still. the Imperial Army isn't retreating.

909
01:10:35.064 --> 01:10:36.941
It's no big deal.

910
01:10:37.024 --> 01:10:38.234
We'll set another explosion.

911
01:10:38.317 --> 01:10:39.443
and that'll settle it.

912
01:10:39.526 --> 01:10:41.237
Right. Noro?

913
01:10:41.904 --> 01:10:44.490
Isn't that suitable?

914
01:10:44.573 --> 01:10:45.699
If it weren't for you.

915
01:10:45.783 --> 01:10:47.534
by now we would all have been given

916
01:10:47.618 --> 01:10:49.286
posthumous names by that lecherous monk.

917
01:10:49.870 --> 01:10:50.996
Hey. Noro.

918
01:10:51.080 --> 01:10:53.999
Can you make more of those firebombs?

919
01:10:56.210 --> 01:10:59.421
There are still some old firebombs
in the storage room.

920
01:11:00.130 --> 01:11:02.383
If we mixed some black water.
they'd turn even better.

921
01:11:03.217 --> 01:11:04.510
Black water?

922
01:11:07.763 --> 01:11:10.015
Hey…

923
01:11:11.433 --> 01:11:12.810
Hey.

924
01:11:13.811 --> 01:11:15.604
What are you doing?

925
01:11:15.688 --> 01:11:17.731
What an unrefined bastard.

926
01:11:18.315 --> 01:11:20.276
Why such a dangerous thing
in a celebratory drink?

927
01:11:20.359 --> 01:11:22.152
It was all a lie.

928
01:11:22.236 --> 01:11:24.488
They have no intention
to pardon our crimes.

929
01:11:25.614 --> 01:11:26.448
Right?

930
01:11:27.866 --> 01:11:30.202
What's this? Out of the blue…

931
01:11:31.245 --> 01:11:32.663
Bastard.

932
01:11:33.497 --> 01:11:35.457
Still with the nonsense?

933
01:11:45.175 --> 01:11:46.802
Wait. have you gone mad?

934
01:11:46.885 --> 01:11:49.388
The crazy ones are these samurai.

935
01:11:49.471 --> 01:11:51.932
They plan to silence us
after the mission is done.

936
01:11:52.474 --> 01:11:53.767
The pardons were a big fat lie.

937
01:11:53.851 --> 01:11:55.227
Don't be a fool!

938
01:11:55.311 --> 01:11:56.729
The Chief himself said…

939
01:11:56.812 --> 01:11:59.690
It's true. I heard it all.

940
01:12:00.733 --> 01:12:01.775
What?

941
01:12:04.611 --> 01:12:05.612
Irie.

942
01:12:06.905 --> 01:12:08.157
Is it true?

943
01:12:10.326 --> 01:12:11.618
No answer?

944
01:12:14.538 --> 01:12:17.458
Do you think you're going to fool us now?

945
01:12:19.543 --> 01:12:21.170
This is no joke.

946
01:12:21.253 --> 01:12:24.965
I don't know a thing!

947
01:12:26.592 --> 01:12:30.304
Irie. why the heck
don't you just say it's a lie?

948
01:12:30.387 --> 01:12:31.263
Irie!

949
01:12:33.098 --> 01:12:34.600
Confess.

950
01:12:44.735 --> 01:12:46.445
It's like he said.

951
01:12:47.780 --> 01:12:50.616
We were notified that
once the criminals are done with the job.

952
01:12:50.699 --> 01:12:52.701
we shall silence them.

953
01:12:59.792 --> 01:13:00.793
What?

954
01:13:08.592 --> 01:13:11.720
Idiot! What do you mean that
the castle has been taken by the Alliance?

955
01:13:12.971 --> 01:13:14.306
I'm ashamed of myself.

956
01:13:14.390 --> 01:13:16.266
An apology won't solve this!

957
01:13:17.434 --> 01:13:19.186
This idiot…

958
01:13:19.269 --> 01:13:20.938
We had no other way

959
01:13:21.021 --> 01:13:23.273
to get to the Imperial Army.

960
01:13:26.068 --> 01:13:27.945
What did you say?

961
01:13:29.780 --> 01:13:31.240
Then. you bastard…

962
01:13:32.324 --> 01:13:35.452
You were planning to deceive
the Alliance from the beginning?

963
01:13:40.416 --> 01:13:43.168
<i>You're deciding the clan's objectives
all of a sudden.</i>

964
01:13:44.294 --> 01:13:46.922
As soon as the Alliance
leaves the castle town.

965
01:13:47.005 --> 01:13:49.216
we are to welcome
the Imperial Army right away…

966
01:13:52.511 --> 01:13:54.346
and surrender without bloodshed.

967
01:13:57.182 --> 01:13:58.183
What?

968
01:14:04.857 --> 01:14:07.860
No. I don't get it.

969
01:14:07.943 --> 01:14:10.529
Why are we carrying
the Alliance flag. then?

970
01:14:11.113 --> 01:14:13.365
If we raised Shibata's flag.

971
01:14:14.032 --> 01:14:17.494
joining the Imperial Army
would become a dificult task.

972
01:14:18.954 --> 01:14:21.957
We were just buying time

973
01:14:22.040 --> 01:14:24.001
until the Alliance leaves the castle.

974
01:14:25.419 --> 01:14:26.587
I understand now.

975
01:14:27.212 --> 01:14:29.423
That's why the bridge
couldn't be destroyed.

976
01:14:30.132 --> 01:14:33.969
At some point you'll have
to welcome the Imperial Army.

977
01:14:34.052 --> 01:14:37.055
But. how could you plan
to join the Imperial Army

978
01:14:37.139 --> 01:14:40.184
when you have killed
many of their men already?

979
01:14:40.267 --> 01:14:41.477
That's why Shibata

980
01:14:41.560 --> 01:14:43.103
cannot let us live after.

981
01:14:45.022 --> 01:14:46.940
Why…

982
01:14:48.108 --> 01:14:50.652
You're not supposed to be the scammers.

983
01:14:55.949 --> 01:14:57.284
You must be kidding.

984
01:14:59.953 --> 01:15:02.748
To say that the Chief lied…

985
01:15:05.792 --> 01:15:07.711
You must be kidding.

986
01:15:08.462 --> 01:15:10.964
But if it weren't for that. you…

987
01:15:11.048 --> 01:15:13.050
To make me wear this…

988
01:15:14.676 --> 01:15:17.387
Am I some Nagaoka monkey?

989
01:15:18.472 --> 01:15:19.890
Don't mess with me!

990
01:15:22.976 --> 01:15:26.313
I'm sorry. Heishiro.

991
01:15:26.897 --> 01:15:29.525
An apology is not enough.

992
01:15:29.608 --> 01:15:30.901
Huh?

993
01:15:30.984 --> 01:15:34.363
We're going to be executed.
no matter how much we apologized…

994
01:15:35.280 --> 01:15:38.659
You're messing around. you bastard!

995
01:15:40.160 --> 01:15:41.620
I'll kill you!

996
01:15:43.622 --> 01:15:45.541
- That bastard!
- Shut up!

997
01:15:46.375 --> 01:15:48.210
Arai. stop it.

998
01:15:48.293 --> 01:15:49.336
Shut it.

999
01:15:50.295 --> 01:15:52.673
How we use a bunch of criminals
condemned to die

1000
01:15:52.756 --> 01:15:54.007
is up to us to decide.

1001
01:15:54.091 --> 01:15:55.300
What are you saying?

1002
01:15:55.384 --> 01:15:57.427
It's extremely disrespectful

1003
01:15:58.011 --> 01:16:00.681
for people like you
to give us your opinion.

1004
01:16:01.848 --> 01:16:03.267
Shut up and obey!

1005
01:16:07.938 --> 01:16:09.064
Irie…

1006
01:16:15.112 --> 01:16:17.531
Irie… What. you…

1007
01:16:38.302 --> 01:16:41.763
I'm sorry we deceived you.

1008
01:16:43.307 --> 01:16:44.641
I…

1009
01:16:45.225 --> 01:16:48.645
I will let you go. no matter what.

1010
01:16:49.479 --> 01:16:51.815
I'll persuade the Chief.

1011
01:16:53.400 --> 01:16:54.526
So…

1012
01:16:58.030 --> 01:16:59.364
This is how it is.

1013
01:17:01.992 --> 01:17:03.869
I'm sorry.

1014
01:17:08.999 --> 01:17:10.125
Hey.

1015
01:17:10.208 --> 01:17:12.544
You really aren't going to believe him.
are you?

1016
01:17:13.378 --> 01:17:17.424
But he's the only one
we can rely on to get our pardon.

1017
01:17:18.967 --> 01:17:20.594
That's the way it is.

1018
01:17:22.971 --> 01:17:25.057
The heck you're saying.
you spineless coward?

1019
01:17:25.140 --> 01:17:26.642
These man fooled us!

1020
01:17:26.725 --> 01:17:28.018
I'm not forgiving him.

1021
01:17:30.312 --> 01:17:31.480
Brother…

1022
01:17:42.658 --> 01:17:43.825
Well. boss.

1023
01:17:49.748 --> 01:17:52.125
I'm not having anything
of what you're saying.

1024
01:17:54.670 --> 01:17:56.463
I'm sorry.

1025
01:17:56.546 --> 01:18:00.258
Please. forgive me…

1026
01:18:51.977 --> 01:18:53.937
It's been two days
since the Suicide Squad was sent.

1027
01:18:54.020 --> 01:18:57.607
It's only a matter of time
before the Imperial Army breaks through.

1028
01:18:57.691 --> 01:18:59.985
If the Alliance
isn't expelled once and for all.

1029
01:19:00.068 --> 01:19:02.863
we will have to face
the Imperial Army in Shibata.

1030
01:19:11.163 --> 01:19:12.581
Kana is gone?

1031
01:19:12.664 --> 01:19:14.040
Her horse isn't here either.

1032
01:19:14.875 --> 01:19:17.794
I asked the servants.
but no one knows anything about it.

1033
01:19:21.423 --> 01:19:23.091
Do you have any idea?

1034
01:19:23.884 --> 01:19:26.636
No. it can't be…

1035
01:19:27.262 --> 01:19:29.931
She's not in the right condition
to overexert herself.

1036
01:19:30.015 --> 01:19:32.225
- If you happened to know…
- Wait.

1037
01:19:32.726 --> 01:19:33.727
What do you mean?

1038
01:19:37.189 --> 01:19:40.609
Kana is with Irie's child…

1039
01:19:42.027 --> 01:19:43.445
What?

1040
01:19:56.917 --> 01:20:00.253
DAY THREE
KEIO 4. 24TH DAY OF THE 7TH MONTH

1041
01:20:09.221 --> 01:20:10.555
Are you awake?

1042
01:20:12.182 --> 01:20:14.392
That's the only way
for us to get our pardons.

1043
01:20:24.361 --> 01:20:25.779
Hey!

1044
01:20:29.199 --> 01:20:32.536
Rebel Army. can you hear us?

1045
01:20:34.329 --> 01:20:37.874
Rebel Army. can you hear us?

1046
01:20:40.961 --> 01:20:44.381
Listen to what I have to say.

1047
01:20:49.553 --> 01:20:52.055
How cruel of them.

1048
01:20:53.598 --> 01:20:54.808
We have no intention at all

1049
01:20:54.891 --> 01:20:57.143
to start a war here in Shibata.

1050
01:20:58.728 --> 01:21:02.816
Release the hostages
and open the gate immediately.

1051
01:21:03.400 --> 01:21:06.653
If you do so.
we'll turn a blind eye on your outrage.

1052
01:21:07.279 --> 01:21:08.196
What?

1053
01:21:08.280 --> 01:21:11.324
If you swear
to die by the Imperial banner.

1054
01:21:11.408 --> 01:21:13.034
all your crimes will be forsaken.

1055
01:21:13.118 --> 01:21:15.328
and we will accept you
as soldiers of the Imperial Army.

1056
01:21:16.037 --> 01:21:16.913
What?

1057
01:21:16.997 --> 01:21:19.124
- You heard that? They want us.
- Quiet.

1058
01:21:20.500 --> 01:21:24.504
But if you choose to ignore us.

1059
01:21:26.172 --> 01:21:29.384
you'll be regarded as rebels and crushed.

1060
01:21:29.968 --> 01:21:31.136
Do you hear?

1061
01:21:31.761 --> 01:21:33.138
We'll await your response.

1062
01:21:36.558 --> 01:21:39.394
Hey. did you hear that?

1063
01:21:39.477 --> 01:21:41.354
We'll get pardoned
if we join the Imperial Army.

1064
01:21:41.438 --> 01:21:42.898
Yes. that's what they said.

1065
01:21:44.608 --> 01:21:46.568
- We're saved.
- Wait.

1066
01:21:47.110 --> 01:21:49.362
The signal fire might light up today.

1067
01:21:49.446 --> 01:21:51.114
What if it doesn't?

1068
01:21:52.699 --> 01:21:54.159
- Well…
- Boss.

1069
01:21:54.242 --> 01:21:55.744
Are you blind or what?

1070
01:21:55.827 --> 01:21:58.705
We don't stand a chance against them.

1071
01:21:58.788 --> 01:22:00.415
Besides. if we join the Imperial Army.

1072
01:22:00.498 --> 01:22:02.417
we could redeem ourselves.

1073
01:22:02.500 --> 01:22:04.377
That's right. boss.

1074
01:22:04.461 --> 01:22:07.505
You were fooled by Shibata's Chief too.
weren't you?

1075
01:22:07.589 --> 01:22:10.050
Wouldn't it be stupid
to fight and die for him?

1076
01:22:14.346 --> 01:22:15.513
Let's go.

1077
01:22:21.603 --> 01:22:23.688
Like they said. we can't beat them.

1078
01:22:24.981 --> 01:22:26.191
Heishiro.

1079
01:22:27.192 --> 01:22:29.486
take these bastards with you.

1080
01:22:31.988 --> 01:22:33.281
What about you?

1081
01:22:35.492 --> 01:22:36.993
I'll stay.

1082
01:22:39.287 --> 01:22:40.622
Do you want to die?

1083
01:22:41.456 --> 01:22:43.583
If the Imperial Army
gets into the castle town

1084
01:22:44.501 --> 01:22:46.419
I'll be dead anyway.

1085
01:22:47.170 --> 01:22:49.756
- Still…
- Grant me at least this.

1086
01:22:51.049 --> 01:22:53.760
Let me be a good son-in-law for the Chief.

1087
01:22:59.349 --> 01:23:00.433
That's what he's saying.

1088
01:23:01.309 --> 01:23:03.061
I'll take their offer.

1089
01:23:04.354 --> 01:23:05.480
Let's go.

1090
01:23:23.415 --> 01:23:24.708
Go. quick.

1091
01:23:35.260 --> 01:23:37.387
Heishiro. what are you doing?

1092
01:23:40.432 --> 01:23:42.475
Are you going to shoot us?

1093
01:23:53.987 --> 01:23:55.280
What's happening?

1094
01:23:58.867 --> 01:24:00.744
Brother!

1095
01:24:04.330 --> 01:24:06.916
The rebels have spoken.

1096
01:24:08.835 --> 01:24:10.128
Get ready!

1097
01:24:10.211 --> 01:24:11.880
- Yes!
- Yes!

1098
01:24:11.963 --> 01:24:13.173
Prepare the cannons!

1099
01:24:22.599 --> 01:24:24.601
What have you done. bastard?

1100
01:24:24.684 --> 01:24:25.894
Hey!

1101
01:24:28.480 --> 01:24:31.816
We can't join the Imperial Army
because you killed that bastard!

1102
01:24:32.358 --> 01:24:34.152
Hey!

1103
01:24:34.235 --> 01:24:37.072
What would happen if we left this place?

1104
01:24:38.865 --> 01:24:40.909
Shibata will be engulfed by the war.

1105
01:24:40.992 --> 01:24:42.786
The castle town will burn to the grounds!

1106
01:24:46.206 --> 01:24:48.249
Your families.

1107
01:24:49.959 --> 01:24:51.878
the villages you were born and raised in.

1108
01:24:54.339 --> 01:24:56.674
everyone could die!

1109
01:25:02.889 --> 01:25:05.141
We have to protect it all.

1110
01:25:31.084 --> 01:25:34.170
Listen up.
this will be a battle of revenge.

1111
01:25:34.796 --> 01:25:37.674
For the honor of our Special Forces!

1112
01:25:37.757 --> 01:25:40.093
We can't lose!

1113
01:25:40.176 --> 01:25:41.845
- Yes. sir!
- Yes. sir!

1114
01:26:03.032 --> 01:26:05.827
Lord Mizoguchi. are you going
to talk to the Young Lord today?

1115
01:26:05.910 --> 01:26:07.704
Move it!

1116
01:26:11.541 --> 01:26:12.750
What's the fuss?

1117
01:26:13.835 --> 01:26:15.461
As you mentioned before.

1118
01:26:15.545 --> 01:26:16.754
our military expeditions

1119
01:26:16.838 --> 01:26:19.299
were being constantly obstructed
by the peasants.

1120
01:26:20.133 --> 01:26:21.551
Kneel down!

1121
01:26:40.236 --> 01:26:43.740
I'll show you
this isn't a convenient solution.

1122
01:26:55.126 --> 01:26:56.502
Destroying the bridge?

1123
01:26:58.213 --> 01:27:00.048
I heard the Imperial Army's infantry

1124
01:27:00.131 --> 01:27:01.841
were ronin or peasants
hired on the battlefield.

1125
01:27:02.425 --> 01:27:04.719
If they can't use their weapons
in the storm. they won't attack.

1126
01:27:05.845 --> 01:27:08.306
Indeed. Then what shall we do?

1127
01:27:10.475 --> 01:27:11.476
Noro.

1128
01:27:12.852 --> 01:27:15.730
will your firebombs light in the rain too?

1129
01:27:17.023 --> 01:27:18.608
They'll do.

1130
01:27:18.691 --> 01:27:20.652
I just mixed in some black water.

1131
01:27:20.735 --> 01:27:22.737
They'll make it through this rain.

1132
01:27:22.820 --> 01:27:23.863
Right. Brother?

1133
01:27:30.245 --> 01:27:32.622
We've got nothing better. Let's do it.

1134
01:27:32.705 --> 01:27:33.665
Right.

1135
01:27:35.541 --> 01:27:36.542
Irie.

1136
01:27:37.210 --> 01:27:38.544
do you mind?

1137
01:27:41.714 --> 01:27:43.716
Good. let's hurry.

1138
01:27:44.425 --> 01:27:45.802
Let's get ready.

1139
01:27:47.679 --> 01:27:49.055
First. the fuses.

1140
01:27:49.138 --> 01:27:51.224
Wrap them in oily paper
so they don't get wet.

1141
01:27:51.307 --> 01:27:52.308
Yes.

1142
01:28:13.538 --> 01:28:14.956
We're holding up.

1143
01:28:15.039 --> 01:28:17.417
Throw in all the firebombs.

1144
01:28:17.500 --> 01:28:19.669
Get ready.

1145
01:28:33.391 --> 01:28:34.642
That idiot.

1146
01:28:43.151 --> 01:28:44.152
What?

1147
01:29:18.686 --> 01:29:19.687
Next!

1148
01:29:24.984 --> 01:29:26.235
Next!

1149
01:29:33.159 --> 01:29:34.494
Hurry!

1150
01:29:35.453 --> 01:29:36.579
Get him!

1151
01:29:36.662 --> 01:29:37.997
Give me your sword!

1152
01:29:39.999 --> 01:29:41.250
Have you gone mad?

1153
01:29:47.256 --> 01:29:48.549
Kazuma.

1154
01:29:51.469 --> 01:29:54.097
Kana? Why…

1155
01:29:55.139 --> 01:29:56.766
Why are you here?

1156
01:29:58.184 --> 01:30:00.561
Because I wanted to see you.

1157
01:30:01.604 --> 01:30:03.773
Go back…

1158
01:30:04.357 --> 01:30:05.983
If you lose your life too.
the Chief will kill me…

1159
01:30:06.067 --> 01:30:07.151
No!

1160
01:30:08.402 --> 01:30:10.029
I'm going to fight here. too.

1161
01:30:13.533 --> 01:30:14.867
Kneel down!

1162
01:30:18.621 --> 01:30:19.914
Hold them!

1163
01:30:19.997 --> 01:30:21.332
Saito.

1164
01:30:22.750 --> 01:30:23.960
Get ready for the battle.

1165
01:30:26.629 --> 01:30:28.297
He'll keep on killing peasants

1166
01:30:28.381 --> 01:30:30.716
until we go out too.

1167
01:30:30.800 --> 01:30:31.968
Next!

1168
01:30:45.064 --> 01:30:46.774
Boss. what's it?

1169
01:30:47.358 --> 01:30:48.484
The main gate…

1170
01:30:56.659 --> 01:30:57.618
Brother.

1171
01:30:58.327 --> 01:30:59.954
He did it again.

1172
01:31:01.622 --> 01:31:02.707
Hey!

1173
01:31:02.790 --> 01:31:04.458
Hey!

1174
01:31:05.668 --> 01:31:07.044
Hey!

1175
01:31:10.840 --> 01:31:13.843
Hey…

1176
01:31:15.720 --> 01:31:17.471
Brother!

1177
01:31:17.555 --> 01:31:18.472
Brother!

1178
01:31:18.556 --> 01:31:20.141
Get back!

1179
01:31:20.224 --> 01:31:21.184
Hurry up!

1180
01:31:21.267 --> 01:31:22.768
Brother.

1181
01:31:23.644 --> 01:31:25.021
- Brother.
- Noro!

1182
01:31:25.605 --> 01:31:27.982
- Brother!
- Oroshiya. get in.

1183
01:31:29.066 --> 01:31:30.610
Isn't the fire out?

1184
01:31:30.693 --> 01:31:32.236
Oroshiya. how's the ember?

1185
01:31:34.405 --> 01:31:35.823
It's still fine.

1186
01:31:39.493 --> 01:31:40.828
Listen!

1187
01:31:45.291 --> 01:31:47.627
Let me join you!

1188
01:31:51.339 --> 01:31:52.548
I have no weapons!

1189
01:31:53.216 --> 01:31:55.968
I really want to join the Imperial Army!

1190
01:31:57.887 --> 01:31:59.222
Look at this!

1191
01:32:04.477 --> 01:32:05.895
The head of a samurai
from the Suicide Squad.

1192
01:32:10.524 --> 01:32:11.901
- Move.
- Move.

1193
01:32:11.984 --> 01:32:13.569
Let go…

1194
01:32:14.237 --> 01:32:15.404
Where are the firebombs?

1195
01:32:15.488 --> 01:32:17.365
- I have them.
- Hurry up!

1196
01:32:18.115 --> 01:32:21.577
Brother…

1197
01:32:30.836 --> 01:32:33.089
I'm saying it hurts!

1198
01:32:33.172 --> 01:32:35.174
Did you cut his head?

1199
01:32:35.258 --> 01:32:36.259
Yes.

1200
01:32:36.926 --> 01:32:38.803
I don't want to obey Shibata anymore.

1201
01:32:40.179 --> 01:32:41.305
Shibata?

1202
01:32:43.474 --> 01:32:45.977
Did you just say Shibata?

1203
01:32:46.769 --> 01:32:49.188
Yes. the people in that fortress.

1204
01:32:58.948 --> 01:33:00.408
- Give it to me.
- Tie it up carefully.

1205
01:33:04.954 --> 01:33:06.163
It's the fuses.

1206
01:33:10.293 --> 01:33:11.168
Tug the fuse.

1207
01:33:12.378 --> 01:33:14.130
Quick!

1208
01:33:20.303 --> 01:33:26.142
It was all a puppet show
from Shibata. right?

1209
01:33:28.477 --> 01:33:30.146
Here. have this.

1210
01:33:32.857 --> 01:33:34.108
What do we do?

1211
01:33:35.276 --> 01:33:37.320
It can't be helped.

1212
01:33:37.403 --> 01:33:41.115
This turned into a war against Shibata.

1213
01:33:41.198 --> 01:33:42.408
Yes.

1214
01:33:43.576 --> 01:33:45.202
Ask me anything about them.

1215
01:33:57.340 --> 01:33:58.632
Do with him as you please.

1216
01:34:05.848 --> 01:34:09.185
Hey. wait! Wait a minute!

1217
01:34:09.268 --> 01:34:10.478
I want to enter the Army!

1218
01:34:12.229 --> 01:34:13.481
I fled the place!

1219
01:34:14.398 --> 01:34:17.526
Let go! I've been fooled!

1220
01:34:19.028 --> 01:34:20.071
Brother…

1221
01:34:20.154 --> 01:34:21.572
Ouch!

1222
01:34:22.323 --> 01:34:23.491
Noro!

1223
01:34:24.575 --> 01:34:25.576
Wait!

1224
01:34:27.661 --> 01:34:29.330
Hey. catch him!

1225
01:34:29.413 --> 01:34:31.415
Stop. Noro! What are you doing?

1226
01:34:32.750 --> 01:34:35.044
Stop. Noro!

1227
01:34:37.046 --> 01:34:38.798
Heishiro. hang on tight!

1228
01:34:39.382 --> 01:34:41.967
- It's not time!
- Noro. wait!

1229
01:34:43.260 --> 01:34:44.845
Get back!

1230
01:34:44.929 --> 01:34:45.805
Quick!

1231
01:34:51.685 --> 01:34:52.686
Quick!

1232
01:34:54.230 --> 01:34:55.272
Hurry!

1233
01:35:05.282 --> 01:35:07.326
Let go…

1234
01:35:07.410 --> 01:35:10.830
Hey! Wait! Wait a minute…

1235
01:35:10.913 --> 01:35:12.206
Be prepared.

1236
01:35:12.289 --> 01:35:15.084
Wait…

1237
01:35:19.463 --> 01:35:20.923
Wait!

1238
01:35:50.911 --> 01:35:52.079
What?

1239
01:35:54.915 --> 01:35:57.168
Brother!

1240
01:35:57.251 --> 01:35:59.587
Brother. are you okay?

1241
01:35:59.670 --> 01:36:01.797
Are you trying to kill me?

1242
01:36:01.881 --> 01:36:03.382
- One more shot. oops!
- Stop!

1243
01:36:07.178 --> 01:36:08.095
The rebels!

1244
01:36:09.555 --> 01:36:11.974
- Those are the rebels!
- Get them!

1245
01:36:12.766 --> 01:36:14.727
Quick. light it up!

1246
01:36:14.810 --> 01:36:17.188
I know. you noisy old man.

1247
01:36:18.898 --> 01:36:20.900
Damn. it's too wet to light up.

1248
01:36:20.983 --> 01:36:22.818
- Give it to me.
- It's Noro!

1249
01:36:29.992 --> 01:36:31.410
We won't make it. light it up quick!

1250
01:36:31.494 --> 01:36:33.245
I know. but it won't light up!

1251
01:36:38.334 --> 01:36:40.753
What are you doing?

1252
01:36:47.593 --> 01:36:48.844
I'll go.

1253
01:36:52.431 --> 01:36:53.724
Wait!

1254
01:36:58.062 --> 01:36:59.146
You…

1255
01:37:00.147 --> 01:37:03.275
That's our amazing Nimaime.

1256
01:37:06.153 --> 01:37:08.697
That will disappear in no time.

1257
01:37:11.283 --> 01:37:13.285
Have my robe.

1258
01:37:29.802 --> 01:37:31.011
Quick. hurry up!

1259
01:37:34.181 --> 01:37:36.308
You. what are you doing?

1260
01:37:40.229 --> 01:37:42.731
Stop. stop!

1261
01:37:42.815 --> 01:37:46.277
Mom. forgive me…

1262
01:37:50.864 --> 01:37:52.324
Stop!

1263
01:38:17.725 --> 01:38:19.685
Noro!

1264
01:38:44.668 --> 01:38:46.337
Chief. the bath is ready.

1265
01:38:46.420 --> 01:38:48.380
There's no guarantee
that cholera won't spread.

1266
01:38:49.173 --> 01:38:51.800
Light the signal fire as soon
as the Alliance leaves the castle.

1267
01:38:51.884 --> 01:38:52.885
Yes.

1268
01:39:15.407 --> 01:39:17.159
We're parting to battle.

1269
01:39:19.161 --> 01:39:20.621
We're going into battle.

1270
01:39:20.704 --> 01:39:22.539
- Yes. sir!
- Yes. sir!

1271
01:39:56.240 --> 01:39:57.366
Kana…

1272
01:39:58.701 --> 01:39:59.702
Yes.

1273
01:40:09.503 --> 01:40:11.004
Give this to Heishiro.

1274
01:40:22.391 --> 01:40:23.726
Kazuma?

1275
01:40:28.188 --> 01:40:29.606
Kazuma…

1276
01:40:31.316 --> 01:40:32.359
No…

1277
01:40:34.737 --> 01:40:35.612
No…

1278
01:40:37.281 --> 01:40:38.991
Kazuma.

1279
01:40:41.034 --> 01:40:42.369
No…

1280
01:40:58.010 --> 01:41:00.804
None of the people
who promised to release us

1281
01:41:01.847 --> 01:41:03.223
is alive anymore.

1282
01:41:04.308 --> 01:41:07.728
The ten of us criminals
have been cut down to a half too.

1283
01:41:10.522 --> 01:41:12.649
Hey. we destroyed the bridge.

1284
01:41:12.733 --> 01:41:14.526
So why are they still sticking around?

1285
01:41:15.444 --> 01:41:17.738
If they can't take
even a fortress like this

1286
01:41:17.821 --> 01:41:19.698
they just can't go back. can they?

1287
01:41:20.616 --> 01:41:22.701
I need a break.

1288
01:41:22.785 --> 01:41:24.661
I don't have any strength left.

1289
01:41:25.913 --> 01:41:29.082
Boss. what do we do?

1290
01:41:29.166 --> 01:41:31.877
The fire signal hasn't lit up at all.

1291
01:41:35.547 --> 01:41:36.673
Who's there?

1292
01:41:41.637 --> 01:41:43.764
That idiot is still alive.

1293
01:41:43.847 --> 01:41:45.140
The tattooed man.

1294
01:41:45.224 --> 01:41:48.769
Oroshiya… Check this man. please.

1295
01:41:49.561 --> 01:41:52.105
Hey. are you okay? Hey!

1296
01:41:53.690 --> 01:41:55.317
Help him. please. Quick…

1297
01:42:13.961 --> 01:42:14.962
What are you doing?

1298
01:42:26.932 --> 01:42:31.144
Why? Why aren't they going to battle?

1299
01:42:50.581 --> 01:42:54.751
We almost got fooled by your puppet show.

1300
01:42:54.835 --> 01:42:56.628
Or that's what I heard.

1301
01:42:58.297 --> 01:43:00.591
You weren’t really planning to ignore

1302
01:43:00.674 --> 01:43:02.843
the Young Lord’s wishes. kick us out.

1303
01:43:03.427 --> 01:43:06.138
and switch sides
to the Imperial Army. were you?

1304
01:43:06.221 --> 01:43:11.310
That the peasants are sick with cholera.
it was all a lie.

1305
01:43:12.644 --> 01:43:14.187
Mizoguchi.

1306
01:43:15.480 --> 01:43:17.024
You were prepared to do

1307
01:43:17.649 --> 01:43:19.192
the harakiri. weren't you?

1308
01:43:38.795 --> 01:43:39.671
Drink this.

1309
01:43:43.717 --> 01:43:45.427
I quit drinking

1310
01:43:47.304 --> 01:43:49.056
the moment I met my wife…

1311
01:44:07.824 --> 01:44:09.242
For Noro.

1312
01:44:09.952 --> 01:44:13.538
it'd been harder if you had died
before him. you know.

1313
01:44:24.591 --> 01:44:26.885
He died protecting his beloved brother.

1314
01:44:29.888 --> 01:44:31.431
As he wished.

1315
01:44:33.892 --> 01:44:35.852
I was fine with dying first.

1316
01:44:40.524 --> 01:44:42.567
Why him of all people…

1317
01:44:47.698 --> 01:44:49.324
Isn't it always like this?

1318
01:44:54.246 --> 01:44:56.123
I bring bad luck to everyone.

1319
01:44:59.918 --> 01:45:02.004
Why didn't I die before him?

1320
01:45:06.550 --> 01:45:07.968
Why?

1321
01:45:17.644 --> 01:45:19.938
Everyone here is the same.

1322
01:45:21.565 --> 01:45:23.567
We did something
we weren't supposed to do…

1323
01:45:27.195 --> 01:45:29.573
But if we hadn't done it.
we couldn't kept on living.

1324
01:45:31.074 --> 01:45:32.993
We're hopeless people.

1325
01:45:41.251 --> 01:45:44.337
Still. we can't give up.

1326
01:45:45.380 --> 01:45:47.090
Should we give up?

1327
01:45:48.050 --> 01:45:49.843
Look. we're still alive.

1328
01:45:52.554 --> 01:45:54.014
Or should we just die

1329
01:45:54.097 --> 01:45:56.099
like beaten dogs?

1330
01:46:02.022 --> 01:46:03.565
Should we just die?

1331
01:46:07.402 --> 01:46:09.237
Should we just die?

1332
01:46:11.073 --> 01:46:12.115
Should we just die?

1333
01:46:12.199 --> 01:46:13.575
That's right.

1334
01:46:15.368 --> 01:46:17.537
You want to go back
and live with your wife. right?

1335
01:46:18.497 --> 01:46:21.083
I want to keep living
doing the things I like. too.

1336
01:46:22.751 --> 01:46:24.753
Should I just die in a place like this?

1337
01:46:32.427 --> 01:46:34.763
Thank God.

1338
01:46:36.223 --> 01:46:40.143
Brother. you're alive.

1339
01:46:45.440 --> 01:46:47.109
Hey. you…

1340
01:46:52.864 --> 01:46:54.449
You…

1341
01:46:54.533 --> 01:46:56.743
Go die. you bastard!

1342
01:46:58.954 --> 01:47:00.455
It hurts.

1343
01:47:12.175 --> 01:47:18.098
<i>Shibata is a good place…</i>

1344
01:47:19.683 --> 01:47:23.895
<i>The east…</i>

1345
01:47:23.979 --> 01:47:27.482
<i>The west…</i>

1346
01:47:28.150 --> 01:47:34.239
<i>The north and the south…</i>

1347
01:47:34.322 --> 01:47:37.993
Kazuma left this for you. Heishiro.

1348
01:47:46.001 --> 01:47:48.128
Noro. what was hell like?

1349
01:47:48.211 --> 01:47:49.254
Were there good women there?

1350
01:47:49.337 --> 01:47:53.175
Oh. there were plenty of lovely women.

1351
01:47:53.884 --> 01:47:55.802
Brother.

1352
01:48:02.684 --> 01:48:04.853
I can't just be sad forever.

1353
01:48:06.938 --> 01:48:08.773
I'll make my father promise

1354
01:48:10.192 --> 01:48:12.235
that he'll release these criminals.

1355
01:48:14.946 --> 01:48:18.658
That was something Irie wished.

1356
01:48:26.958 --> 01:48:29.211
Brother. brother.

1357
01:48:30.587 --> 01:48:32.380
- I don't dance.
- Come on.

1358
01:48:32.464 --> 01:48:34.132
Dance.

1359
01:48:40.096 --> 01:48:43.141
It stinks! What is this?

1360
01:48:43.225 --> 01:48:45.393
Did you steal it from the Imperial Army?

1361
01:48:46.519 --> 01:48:49.481
Are they drinking
rotting water or something?

1362
01:48:51.316 --> 01:48:53.777
Noro. this is water
from behind the mountain. right?

1363
01:48:55.070 --> 01:48:56.571
It's black water.

1364
01:49:01.952 --> 01:49:03.870
What's that?

1365
01:49:04.579 --> 01:49:08.250
The mountains around here
have black water springing up.

1366
01:49:08.333 --> 01:49:09.626
Right. Brother?

1367
01:49:09.709 --> 01:49:10.877
I told you. I don't know.

1368
01:49:12.379 --> 01:49:13.838
Hey. Noro.

1369
01:49:13.922 --> 01:49:17.217
Did you by any chance
put this water into the firebombs?

1370
01:49:17.300 --> 01:49:20.637
Yes. that's why they light up
even in the rain.

1371
01:49:23.348 --> 01:49:25.183
Could it be…

1372
01:49:26.059 --> 01:49:27.644
an oil well?

1373
01:49:28.812 --> 01:49:30.522
That mine…

1374
01:49:36.987 --> 01:49:39.114
It's right above the enemy.

1375
01:49:40.490 --> 01:49:43.243
Noro. is the well there?

1376
01:49:44.911 --> 01:49:47.664
I went with my brother to take oil…

1377
01:49:47.747 --> 01:49:50.000
Why didn't you tell us earlier?

1378
01:49:50.625 --> 01:49:52.460
Had we thrown a firebomb there
from the start.

1379
01:49:52.544 --> 01:49:54.838
it would've spared us all this trouble.

1380
01:49:55.672 --> 01:49:59.676
Idiot. if we could have done just that…

1381
01:49:59.759 --> 01:50:00.969
We can.

1382
01:50:02.137 --> 01:50:04.597
We can burn them all.

1383
01:50:05.974 --> 01:50:06.975
Shall we?

1384
01:50:09.686 --> 01:50:10.854
Fool…

1385
01:50:11.604 --> 01:50:13.940
We destroyed the bridge.

1386
01:50:15.525 --> 01:50:18.987
Good grief.
we forgot the most important part.

1387
01:50:19.571 --> 01:50:21.156
We could cross the river.

1388
01:50:22.198 --> 01:50:23.992
It's not like the rope fell completely.

1389
01:50:24.075 --> 01:50:26.202
An army couldn't cross. but we can.

1390
01:50:26.995 --> 01:50:28.747
Let's do it. boss.

1391
01:50:29.998 --> 01:50:33.126
Do you mean you want to burn that well?

1392
01:50:33.877 --> 01:50:35.045
I don't think the Imperial Army

1393
01:50:35.128 --> 01:50:36.504
is going to attack today of all days.

1394
01:50:36.588 --> 01:50:37.797
Now's our chance.

1395
01:50:38.757 --> 01:50:40.717
We are villains. after all.

1396
01:50:41.301 --> 01:50:42.594
Battle or no battle.

1397
01:50:42.677 --> 01:50:44.137
we're all going to be beheaded.

1398
01:50:45.805 --> 01:50:47.098
Still. I won't consent to being

1399
01:50:47.182 --> 01:50:48.600
treated as a bug and left to die.

1400
01:50:53.229 --> 01:50:55.648
Be it the Imperial Army or the rebels.

1401
01:50:57.275 --> 01:50:59.527
I've had enough of being trampled on.

1402
01:51:00.695 --> 01:51:02.864
I can't help the urge
to knock them all out.

1403
01:51:04.074 --> 01:51:06.659
Boss. let's do it.

1404
01:51:12.874 --> 01:51:14.209
Our last move.

1405
01:51:15.502 --> 01:51:17.295
Let's show them our rebel will.

1406
01:51:26.137 --> 01:51:30.058
What's happening?
The winds are blowing suddenly.

1407
01:51:47.784 --> 01:51:48.785
I'll go.

1408
01:52:33.246 --> 01:52:36.416
Go. You ought to get back
to the castle town before dawn.

1409
01:52:37.000 --> 01:52:38.001
Yes.

1410
01:54:06.339 --> 01:54:08.049
Was it a trick from Shibata?

1411
01:54:08.633 --> 01:54:09.634
Yes.

1412
01:54:11.719 --> 01:54:12.845
I see.

1413
01:54:13.638 --> 01:54:17.892
So you never intended to fight us
from the start. right?

1414
01:54:18.810 --> 01:54:20.979
- Prepare the horses!
- Yes.

1415
01:54:21.062 --> 01:54:24.649
This fortress is just a decoy to stop us.

1416
01:54:24.732 --> 01:54:28.236
We'll get around the fortress
and get to Shibata…

1417
01:54:28.903 --> 01:54:30.530
Lord Yamagata!

1418
01:54:31.656 --> 01:54:33.825
The Alliance is in the castle town.

1419
01:54:34.409 --> 01:54:36.202
Give them this castle.

1420
01:54:36.286 --> 01:54:39.372
We'll move on to Shibata
and take the port.

1421
01:54:39.455 --> 01:54:40.832
Sir.

1422
01:54:40.915 --> 01:54:43.042
- Go!
- Yes. sir!

1423
01:55:13.489 --> 01:55:14.532
It's the black water.

1424
01:55:15.366 --> 01:55:16.784
Good. let's dig it.

1425
01:56:14.258 --> 01:56:16.386
Lord Saito! Lord Irobe!

1426
01:56:18.721 --> 01:56:19.722
What is it?

1427
01:56:22.558 --> 01:56:24.435
Nagaoka Castle is under attack.

1428
01:56:24.519 --> 01:56:27.981
What? The castle is under attack?

1429
01:56:28.064 --> 01:56:30.858
Yes. I heard
that they crossed Haccho-oki.

1430
01:56:30.942 --> 01:56:34.070
and now the whole army
is coming to retake Nagaoka Castle

1431
01:56:34.654 --> 01:56:36.197
We have to fight them.

1432
01:56:36.948 --> 01:56:39.784
Saito. let's go.

1433
01:57:01.097 --> 01:57:02.473
Wait.

1434
01:57:03.099 --> 01:57:05.268
Wait. Takumi.

1435
01:57:08.354 --> 01:57:12.025
If you died. what would become of me?

1436
01:57:20.908 --> 01:57:24.120
No matter how much we dig.
there's no oil coming out.

1437
01:57:24.203 --> 01:57:25.955
It's alright. just shut up
and keep digging.

1438
01:57:34.464 --> 01:57:37.341
What's wrong. Noro?

1439
01:57:40.803 --> 01:57:41.846
Here.

1440
01:58:03.993 --> 01:58:05.870
It came out!

1441
01:58:12.460 --> 01:58:15.046
It stinks!

1442
01:58:31.312 --> 01:58:33.981
Lord Iwamura! Lord Sugiyama!

1443
01:58:38.736 --> 01:58:41.364
The Alliance is attacking the castle?

1444
01:58:41.447 --> 01:58:42.365
Yes.

1445
01:58:42.448 --> 01:58:45.493
Lord Yamagata. you're expected
to join them immediately.

1446
01:58:45.576 --> 01:58:47.245
Am I the monkey of Shibata or something?

1447
01:58:48.287 --> 01:58:49.664
Until I beat them down.

1448
01:58:49.747 --> 01:58:51.457
the beast in me won't calm down.

1449
01:58:54.293 --> 01:58:55.294
Brother.

1450
01:58:58.172 --> 01:58:59.173
Give me fire.

1451
01:59:11.644 --> 01:59:13.479
Watch this. filthy bastards.

1452
01:59:37.295 --> 01:59:38.838
Run!

1453
01:59:38.921 --> 01:59:41.007
- Run!
- Run!

1454
02:00:03.321 --> 02:00:04.739
Serves you right.

1455
02:00:33.392 --> 02:00:34.393
Noro!

1456
02:00:35.937 --> 02:00:37.146
Are you okay?

1457
02:00:39.106 --> 02:00:40.107
Over here!

1458
02:00:45.238 --> 02:00:47.740
- Capture the rebels!
- Yes!

1459
02:00:47.823 --> 02:00:49.784
- Kill them.
- Kill them!

1460
02:01:16.686 --> 02:01:17.895
Well. let's go.

1461
02:01:17.979 --> 02:01:19.313
Go.

1462
02:01:47.341 --> 02:01:48.676
Oroshiya!

1463
02:01:50.052 --> 02:01:51.971
- Are you okay?
- Are you okay!

1464
02:01:55.391 --> 02:01:57.393
You rebels…

1465
02:02:04.400 --> 02:02:06.527
- Noro!
- Brother!

1466
02:02:18.164 --> 02:02:19.582
Let's run. quick!

1467
02:02:20.499 --> 02:02:22.043
Leave me and run away.

1468
02:02:22.752 --> 02:02:24.045
What are you saying?

1469
02:02:24.128 --> 02:02:26.756
I won't be able to be a doctor anymore.

1470
02:02:26.839 --> 02:02:28.924
- Don't say that…
- Run!

1471
02:02:29.008 --> 02:02:30.926
Let's run away together!

1472
02:02:35.806 --> 02:02:37.141
Where are you going?

1473
02:02:37.224 --> 02:02:40.436
I'm finishing this pointless battle.

1474
02:02:40.519 --> 02:02:42.021
Hey. Oroshiya!

1475
02:02:47.818 --> 02:02:49.487
Oroshiya!

1476
02:02:55.785 --> 02:02:58.245
Bastard!

1477
02:03:03.000 --> 02:03:05.336
Let's go. quick!

1478
02:03:15.096 --> 02:03:16.889
Noro. you go first!

1479
02:03:16.972 --> 02:03:20.017
- Brother?
- I'll be there. Now. go!

1480
02:03:33.572 --> 02:03:34.907
You rebels…

1481
02:03:37.201 --> 02:03:38.577
Brother!

1482
02:03:39.662 --> 02:03:42.623
Go. Noro! Run!

1483
02:03:49.713 --> 02:03:52.550
Get lost. you lying bastard!

1484
02:04:01.016 --> 02:04:02.351
Move aside. old man!

1485
02:04:15.156 --> 02:04:17.324
Hey. give me that.

1486
02:04:20.661 --> 02:04:21.996
You. old fool!

1487
02:04:25.249 --> 02:04:28.377
I'm a former spear instructor from Choshu.

1488
02:04:28.461 --> 02:04:30.171
My name is Kohachiro Oshiba.

1489
02:04:31.172 --> 02:04:32.173
For the sake of justice.

1490
02:04:33.924 --> 02:04:36.927
I'm opposing my country.

1491
02:05:21.055 --> 02:05:22.473
Sugiyama…

1492
02:06:25.536 --> 02:06:27.288
You monkey.

1493
02:06:33.752 --> 02:06:34.753
Boss. move!

1494
02:06:41.218 --> 02:06:43.554
Sugiyama! Hey. Sugiyama!

1495
02:06:45.472 --> 02:06:48.434
Sugiyama… Sugiyama!

1496
02:07:01.530 --> 02:07:03.866
Sugiyama!

1497
02:07:06.243 --> 02:07:07.494
Brother!

1498
02:07:07.578 --> 02:07:09.121
Quick! Hurry!

1499
02:07:09.204 --> 02:07:10.831
Quick!…

1500
02:07:12.833 --> 02:07:15.336
- Let's run!
- Run!

1501
02:07:45.574 --> 02:07:49.078
DAY FOUR
KEIO 4. 25TH DAY OF THE 7TH MONTH

1502
02:07:51.997 --> 02:07:53.666
Thank God you're safe.

1503
02:07:55.084 --> 02:07:57.878
I'm really sorry about Lord Irie.

1504
02:07:59.463 --> 02:08:04.385
I have a plea on behalf of Heishiro
and the people who fought with him

1505
02:08:05.219 --> 02:08:08.430
in that fortress. Please. have mercy…

1506
02:08:09.264 --> 02:08:12.559
I know…

1507
02:08:17.439 --> 02:08:21.360
Chief. the Imperial Army is in the castle.

1508
02:08:43.966 --> 02:08:45.342
Young Lord.

1509
02:08:46.385 --> 02:08:50.848
You already know why we are here. do you?

1510
02:08:56.311 --> 02:08:57.479
Yes.

1511
02:08:57.563 --> 02:09:00.733
My lord has made up his mind to cooperate
with the Imperial Army.

1512
02:09:01.817 --> 02:09:04.611
If there's anything
we could do for Shibata…

1513
02:09:08.991 --> 02:09:11.201
There's one thing I'd like to ask
before we get to it.

1514
02:09:18.250 --> 02:09:20.627
The ones who made this seal.

1515
02:09:31.847 --> 02:09:34.558
Still. it feels good. doesn't it?

1516
02:09:35.392 --> 02:09:38.812
It's such a nice weather
for getting back to the castle town.

1517
02:09:57.122 --> 02:09:58.665
Are you going back to the castle town?

1518
02:10:02.044 --> 02:10:04.505
No. I'm not going to Shibata.

1519
02:10:05.506 --> 02:10:08.300
After I get back to my wife…

1520
02:10:09.635 --> 02:10:11.553
Well. let it be whatever it is.

1521
02:10:14.681 --> 02:10:15.724
I see…

1522
02:10:17.226 --> 02:10:18.977
You can't forgive Shibata.

1523
02:10:21.271 --> 02:10:23.190
You should have gotten to know me by now.

1524
02:10:27.277 --> 02:10:30.280
What will Noro do?

1525
02:10:31.532 --> 02:10:33.450
If his brother isn't here.
he'll make a ruckus.

1526
02:10:35.911 --> 02:10:37.412
I'm not his brother.

1527
02:10:45.128 --> 02:10:46.213
Thank you for everything.

1528
02:10:50.092 --> 02:10:51.218
Take care.

1529
02:11:21.206 --> 02:11:24.418
No. I've got nothing left…

1530
02:11:25.043 --> 02:11:26.920
I'll take your offerings…

1531
02:11:28.589 --> 02:11:29.840
Excuse me.

1532
02:11:38.557 --> 02:11:40.392
Hey. wait a minute.

1533
02:11:43.896 --> 02:11:45.647
What was that? Damn…

1534
02:12:58.804 --> 02:13:02.015
Well. let's head back to the castle town.

1535
02:13:04.476 --> 02:13:06.061
I'm staying here.

1536
02:13:07.104 --> 02:13:08.855
Many people have died.

1537
02:13:09.481 --> 02:13:11.066
I'll give them some prayers.

1538
02:13:12.401 --> 02:13:14.319
That sounds like something
a monk would say. right?

1539
02:13:29.960 --> 02:13:31.503
They're here. boss.

1540
02:13:31.586 --> 02:13:34.006
There's no doubt. that's Shibata's flag.

1541
02:13:34.589 --> 02:13:35.716
Hey!

1542
02:13:35.799 --> 02:13:37.843
The young lady told them about us.

1543
02:13:37.926 --> 02:13:41.054
Hey. we're the Suicide Squad!

1544
02:13:41.138 --> 02:13:42.639
Hey!

1545
02:13:43.765 --> 02:13:45.225
Hey!

1546
02:13:58.780 --> 02:13:59.823
Run!

1547
02:14:00.615 --> 02:14:02.701
Run! Run!

1548
02:14:03.285 --> 02:14:04.661
Fire!

1549
02:14:07.581 --> 02:14:08.623
Brother!

1550
02:14:11.084 --> 02:14:12.210
Noro!

1551
02:14:20.218 --> 02:14:22.262
Wait! We're the Suicide Squad!

1552
02:14:23.096 --> 02:14:24.139
Fire!

1553
02:14:27.976 --> 02:14:30.062
We're Shibata's infantry!

1554
02:14:30.645 --> 02:14:32.064
Can't you hear us?

1555
02:14:35.984 --> 02:14:38.445
Come… Come on!

1556
02:14:40.030 --> 02:14:41.698
We fought for Shibata.

1557
02:14:42.365 --> 02:14:44.159
and for our country!

1558
02:15:02.636 --> 02:15:04.679
Stop!

1559
02:15:42.467 --> 02:15:43.760
Lord Washio!

1560
02:15:45.428 --> 02:15:49.474
I was asked by Kana to have mercy on you.

1561
02:15:50.725 --> 02:15:51.893
Do not worry.

1562
02:15:56.523 --> 02:15:58.817
Are there still criminals left?

1563
02:16:08.827 --> 02:16:09.995
Lord Washio?

1564
02:16:11.580 --> 02:16:15.584
I cannot forgive a coward like you.

1565
02:16:19.212 --> 02:16:20.881
You're saying you won't obey?

1566
02:16:22.549 --> 02:16:26.511
Then. deal with him
like you've done with the criminals.

1567
02:16:30.182 --> 02:16:31.558
I don't care.

1568
02:16:32.976 --> 02:16:34.853
I'm a rebel.

1569
02:16:37.772 --> 02:16:39.900
The 11th one.

1570
02:16:41.735 --> 02:16:42.819
Slash him away!

1571
02:17:04.507 --> 02:17:06.343
Fire! Shoot him to death!

1572
02:17:15.769 --> 02:17:16.645
Fire!

1573
02:17:26.947 --> 02:17:27.948
- Let's go.
- Yes.

1574
02:18:36.433 --> 02:18:38.143
Slash him away!

1575
02:18:38.226 --> 02:18:39.269
Yes!

1576
02:18:40.979 --> 02:18:43.481
Noro. do you have any firebombs left?

1577
02:18:43.565 --> 02:18:46.943
The ones that got damp
are in the storage room.

1578
02:18:47.027 --> 02:18:48.987
but I don't know if they'll burn.

1579
02:18:54.617 --> 02:18:56.077
Brother!

1580
02:19:02.334 --> 02:19:03.335
Where?

1581
02:19:09.341 --> 02:19:12.177
Noro. go to the river from the back.

1582
02:19:12.260 --> 02:19:13.845
If you do down the river
you'll get to Shibata.

1583
02:19:14.596 --> 02:19:15.972
What about you. brother?

1584
02:19:18.308 --> 02:19:19.309
I'll go later.

1585
02:19:20.226 --> 02:19:22.062
No. I want to stay with you. brother…

1586
02:19:22.145 --> 02:19:24.105
Don't say foolish things.
it's not like you.

1587
02:19:24.189 --> 02:19:26.983
You can escape. right?

1588
02:19:29.027 --> 02:19:31.780
No… I don't want to leave you.

1589
02:19:31.863 --> 02:19:33.615
Listen to what your brother is saying!

1590
02:19:34.908 --> 02:19:36.785
You've saved me countless times.

1591
02:19:38.912 --> 02:19:41.039
At least at the end.
let me do something a brother would do.

1592
02:19:46.294 --> 02:19:48.671
Come on. go!

1593
02:19:49.798 --> 02:19:51.007
Go!

1594
02:20:13.446 --> 02:20:15.115
Mizoguchi.

1595
02:20:16.825 --> 02:20:18.785
Get your sword!

1596
02:22:06.017 --> 02:22:07.268
Damn.

1597
02:22:27.330 --> 02:22:28.790
Get rid of all of them!

1598
02:22:29.374 --> 02:22:30.667
Yes!

1599
02:22:31.501 --> 02:22:34.379
- Bastard!
- Go. shoot him!

1600
02:22:39.300 --> 02:22:40.718
Don't let him escape!

1601
02:22:47.767 --> 02:22:49.811
Brother! Brother!

1602
02:22:53.439 --> 02:22:55.149
He ran away!

1603
02:22:56.150 --> 02:22:57.360
Go up!

1604
02:23:00.113 --> 02:23:01.531
Fire!

1605
02:23:04.450 --> 02:23:06.119
This is no joke.

1606
02:23:09.080 --> 02:23:10.748
This is no joke.

1607
02:23:15.795 --> 02:23:17.171
That bastard…

1608
02:23:17.922 --> 02:23:20.466
He killed them all.

1609
02:23:41.821 --> 02:23:44.240
Go die!

1610
02:24:04.469 --> 02:24:05.553
Brother…

1611
02:24:08.264 --> 02:24:11.100
Brother!

1612
02:25:02.902 --> 02:25:05.321
We. the people of Shibata.
for the Emperor.

1613
02:25:05.405 --> 02:25:06.948
and for the new Japan.

1614
02:25:07.824 --> 02:25:10.535
are to raise the country
and defeat the rebels.

1615
02:25:11.953 --> 02:25:15.289
How can you say such nonsense
while putting up such an act?

1616
02:25:15.373 --> 02:25:17.375
Enough. Iwamura.

1617
02:25:18.626 --> 02:25:20.211
With Shibata's cooperation.

1618
02:25:20.294 --> 02:25:21.504
we were able to win

1619
02:25:21.587 --> 02:25:24.424
the hearts of the Alliance.

